1
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:31,460
<i>The Tesseract has awakened.</i>

2
00:00:31,460 --> 00:00:33,295
<i>The Tesseract has awakened.</i>

3
00:00:33,296 --> 00:00:38,255
It is on a little world, a human world.

4
00:00:38,969 --> 00:00:42,301
They would wield its power,

5
00:00:42,680 --> 00:00:48,350
but our ally knows its
workings as they never will.

6
00:00:49,896 --> 00:00:52,981
<i>He is ready to lead</i>

7
00:00:53,192 --> 00:00:58,612
<i>and our force, our Chitauri, will follow.</i>

8
00:01:00,240 --> 00:01:02,613
<i>A world will be his.</i>

9
00:01:02,826 --> 00:01:05,947
<i>The universe, yours.</i>

10
00:01:06,164 --> 00:01:12,036
<i>And the humans,
what can they do but burn?</i>

11
00:01:26,268 --> 00:01:27,518
<i>All personnel,</i>

12
00:01:27,519 --> 00:01:29,807
<i>the evacuation order
has been confirmed.</i>

13
00:02:01,721 --> 00:02:03,388
How bad is it?

14
00:02:03,388 --> 00:02:06,674
That's the problem, sir. We don't know.

15
00:02:10,271 --> 00:02:13,188
Dr Selvig read an energy surge
from the Tesseract four hours ago.

16
00:02:13,316 --> 00:02:15,316
NASA didn't authorise Selvig
to go to test phase.

17
00:02:15,401 --> 00:02:17,560
He wasn't testing it.
He wasn't even in the room.

18
00:02:17,778 --> 00:02:18,945
Spontaneous event.

19
00:02:18,947 --> 00:02:20,281
It just turned itself on?

20
00:02:20,282 --> 00:02:21,532
Where are the energy levels now?

21
00:02:21,533 --> 00:02:23,692
Climbing. When Selvig couldn't
shut it down, we ordered evac.

22
00:02:23,911 --> 00:02:25,328
How long to get everyone out?

23
00:02:25,329 --> 00:02:26,871
Campus should be clear
in the next half-hour.

24
00:02:26,872 --> 00:02:28,872
Do better.

25
00:02:29,082 --> 00:02:31,082
Sir, evacuation may be futile.

26
00:02:31,251 --> 00:02:32,835
We should tell them
to go back to sleep?

27
00:02:32,836 --> 00:02:35,043
If we can't control
the Tesseract's energy,

28
00:02:35,254 --> 00:02:37,581
there may not be
a minimum safe distance.

29
00:02:37,716 --> 00:02:38,883
I need you to make sure

30
00:02:38,884 --> 00:02:40,718
the Phase 2 prototypes
are shipped out.

31
00:02:40,719 --> 00:02:42,759
Sir, is that really a priority right now?

32
00:02:42,972 --> 00:02:44,805
Until such time as the world ends,

33
00:02:44,807 --> 00:02:46,847
we will act as though
it intends to spin on.

34
00:02:47,810 --> 00:02:49,394
Clear out the tech below.

35
00:02:49,395 --> 00:02:51,887
Every piece of Phase 2
on a truck and gone.

36
00:02:52,106 --> 00:02:53,606
Yes, sir.

37
00:02:53,608 --> 00:02:55,608
With me.

38
00:02:57,861 --> 00:02:59,861
Talk to me, Doctor.

39
00:03:00,656 --> 00:03:02,240
Director.

40
00:03:02,241 --> 00:03:04,116
Is there anything we know for certain?

41
00:03:04,117 --> 00:03:06,360
The Tesseract is misbehaving.

42
00:03:06,579 --> 00:03:09,366
- Is that supposed to be funny?
- No, it's not funny at all.

43
00:03:09,582 --> 00:03:13,081
The Tesseract is not only
active, she's behaving.

44
00:03:13,294 --> 00:03:14,503
I assume you pulled the plug.

45
00:03:14,504 --> 00:03:16,421
She's an energy source.

46
00:03:16,423 --> 00:03:19,460
We turn off the power,
she turns it back on.

47
00:03:19,676 --> 00:03:20,968
If she reaches peak level...

48
00:03:20,969 --> 00:03:24,384
We prepared for this, Doctor.
Harnessing energy from space.

49
00:03:24,598 --> 00:03:26,098
But we don't have the harness.

50
00:03:26,098 --> 00:03:27,933
My calculations are far from complete.

51
00:03:27,935 --> 00:03:30,473
And she's throwing off
interference, radiation.

52
00:03:30,687 --> 00:03:32,687
Nothing harmful,
low levels of gamma radiation.

53
00:03:33,314 --> 00:03:35,314
That can be harmful.

54
00:03:35,359 --> 00:03:36,942
Where's Agent Barton?

55
00:03:36,944 --> 00:03:38,944
The Hawk?

56
00:03:39,530 --> 00:03:41,569
Up in his nest, as usual.

57
00:03:43,033 --> 00:03:45,033
<i>Agent Barton, report.</i>

58
00:03:45,704 --> 00:03:46,996
<i>I gave you this detail</i>

59
00:03:46,997 --> 00:03:48,788
<i>so you could keep
a close eye on things.</i>

60
00:03:48,789 --> 00:03:50,373
Well, I see better from a distance.

61
00:03:50,375 --> 00:03:52,375
Have you seen anything
that might set this thing off?

62
00:03:52,793 --> 00:03:54,917
Doctor, it's spiking again.

63
00:03:55,128 --> 00:03:56,712
No one's come or gone.

64
00:03:56,713 --> 00:03:58,549
And Selvig's clean.

65
00:03:58,550 --> 00:04:00,838
No contacts, no IMs.

66
00:04:01,343 --> 00:04:03,343
If there was any tampering,
sir, it wasn't at this end.

67
00:04:05,056 --> 00:04:06,640
"At this end"?

68
00:04:06,641 --> 00:04:10,473
Yeah, the Cube is a doorway to
the other end of space, right?

69
00:04:12,313 --> 00:04:14,313
Doors open from both sides.

70
00:04:14,358 --> 00:04:16,358
Not yet.

71
00:05:23,596 --> 00:05:26,716
Sir, please put down the spear.

72
00:06:06,057 --> 00:06:08,057
You have heart.

73
00:06:37,797 --> 00:06:39,797
Please don't.

74
00:06:41,091 --> 00:06:42,509
I still need that.

75
00:06:42,509 --> 00:06:44,177
This doesn't have to get any messier.

76
00:06:44,178 --> 00:06:45,596
Of course it does.

77
00:06:45,596 --> 00:06:47,596
I've come too far for anything else.

78
00:06:49,433 --> 00:06:52,221
I am Loki, of Asgard

79
00:06:52,937 --> 00:06:55,310
and I am burdened with
glorious purpose.

80
00:06:55,524 --> 00:06:57,442
Loki,

81
00:06:57,442 --> 00:06:58,944
brother of Thor.

82
00:06:58,944 --> 00:07:01,399
We have no quarrel with your people.

83
00:07:01,612 --> 00:07:04,567
An ant has no quarrel with a boot.

84
00:07:05,158 --> 00:07:07,158
Are you planning to step on us?

85
00:07:07,161 --> 00:07:10,245
I come with glad tidings

86
00:07:11,499 --> 00:07:13,499
of a world made free.

87
00:07:13,793 --> 00:07:15,000
Free from what?

88
00:07:15,002 --> 00:07:16,877
Freedom.

89
00:07:16,879 --> 00:07:19,500
Freedom is life's great lie.

90
00:07:19,716 --> 00:07:23,132
Once you accept that, in your heart,

91
00:07:27,641 --> 00:07:29,641
you will know peace.

92
00:07:29,809 --> 00:07:32,264
Yeah, you say "peace,"

93
00:07:32,478 --> 00:07:34,478
I kind of think you mean the other thing.

94
00:07:34,521 --> 00:07:37,012
Sir, Director Fury is stalling.

95
00:07:37,233 --> 00:07:38,692
This place is about to blow

96
00:07:38,692 --> 00:07:40,692
and drop a hundred feet of rock on us.

97
00:07:41,904 --> 00:07:43,154
He means to bury us.

98
00:07:43,156 --> 00:07:44,490
Like the pharaohs of old.

99
00:07:44,490 --> 00:07:46,490
He's right. The portal
is collapsing in on itself.

100
00:07:46,659 --> 00:07:48,867
We've got maybe two minutes
before this goes critical.

101
00:07:49,245 --> 00:07:51,245
Well, then.

102
00:08:06,012 --> 00:08:08,012
I need these vehicles.

103
00:08:11,185 --> 00:08:13,307
- Who's that?
- They didn't tell me.

104
00:08:16,524 --> 00:08:18,192
<i>Hill!</i>

105
00:08:18,192 --> 00:08:20,192
Do you copy?

106
00:08:20,194 --> 00:08:22,194
<i>Barton has turned.</i>

107
00:08:34,584 --> 00:08:37,419
They have the Tesseract!
Shut them down!

108
00:09:13,833 --> 00:09:16,039
Okay, let's go. No, leave it. Go!

109
00:09:32,519 --> 00:09:34,642
We're clear upstairs, sir.
You need to go.

110
00:11:06,615 --> 00:11:08,283
<i>Director?</i>

111
00:11:08,283 --> 00:11:09,993
Director Fury, do you copy?

112
00:11:09,994 --> 00:11:12,283
The Tesseract is with a hostile force.

113
00:11:12,538 --> 00:11:14,946
I have men down. Hill?

114
00:11:15,292 --> 00:11:17,292
A lot of men still under.

115
00:11:17,376 --> 00:11:19,294
I don't know how many survivors.

116
00:11:19,296 --> 00:11:20,671
<i>Sound a general call.</i>

117
00:11:20,672 --> 00:11:22,506
I want every living soul
not working rescue

118
00:11:22,508 --> 00:11:23,716
looking for that briefcase.

119
00:11:23,716 --> 00:11:24,967
Roger that.

120
00:11:24,969 --> 00:11:28,254
Coulson, get back to base.
This is a Level Seven.

121
00:11:29,347 --> 00:11:31,140
<i>As of right now,</i>

122
00:11:31,142 --> 00:11:33,142
we are at war.

123
00:11:34,311 --> 00:11:36,311
What do we do?

124
00:12:12,475 --> 00:12:16,177
This is not how I wanted this evening
to go.

125
00:12:16,312 --> 00:12:18,147
I know how you wanted this evening
to go.

126
00:12:18,148 --> 00:12:19,356
Believe me

127
00:12:19,357 --> 00:12:21,357
this is better.

128
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:23,360
Who are you working for?

129
00:12:23,613 --> 00:12:25,613
Lermentov, yes?

130
00:12:27,157 --> 00:12:29,157
Does he think

131
00:12:29,243 --> 00:12:31,243
we have to go through him

132
00:12:31,327 --> 00:12:33,327
to move our cargo?

133
00:12:34,038 --> 00:12:38,582
I thought General Solohob
is in charge of the export business.

134
00:12:38,919 --> 00:12:40,919
Solohob

135
00:12:41,088 --> 00:12:43,128
a bagman, a front.

136
00:12:45,592 --> 00:12:49,756
Your outdated information betrays you.

137
00:12:51,350 --> 00:12:54,100
The famous Black Widow

138
00:12:55,769 --> 00:13:00,147
and she turns out to be
simply another pretty face.

139
00:13:01,025 --> 00:13:04,192
You really think I'm pretty?

140
00:13:06,740 --> 00:13:08,981
Tell Lermentov we don't need him

141
00:13:09,283 --> 00:13:12,866
to move the tanks.

142
00:13:13,831 --> 00:13:16,451
Tell him he is out.

143
00:13:16,875 --> 00:13:18,875
Well...

144
00:13:21,379 --> 00:13:23,379
...you may have to write it down.

145
00:13:32,099 --> 00:13:34,099
It's for her.

146
00:13:37,020 --> 00:13:38,437
You listen carefully

147
00:13:38,438 --> 00:13:41,013
<i>You're at 1- 14
Silensky Plaza, 3rd floor.</i>

148
00:13:41,275 --> 00:13:43,399
<i>We have an F-22
exactly eight miles out.</i>

149
00:13:44,278 --> 00:13:46,278
<i>Put the woman on the phone,
or I will blow up the block</i>

150
00:13:46,447 --> 00:13:48,486
<i>before you can make the lobby.</i>

151
00:13:54,956 --> 00:13:57,078
<i>- We need you to come in.
- Are you kidding? I'm working.</i>

152
00:13:57,292 --> 00:13:58,793
<i>This takes precedence.</i>

153
00:13:58,793 --> 00:14:00,586
I'm in the middle of an interrogation.

154
00:14:00,586 --> 00:14:02,586
This moron is giving me everything.

155
00:14:02,798 --> 00:14:05,418
I don't give everything.

156
00:14:06,844 --> 00:14:08,344
Look, you can't pull me
out of this right now.

157
00:14:08,345 --> 00:14:10,345
<i>Natasha...</i>

158
00:14:10,931 --> 00:14:12,931
Barton's been compromised.

159
00:14:15,644 --> 00:14:17,644
Let me put you on hold.

160
00:14:59,230 --> 00:15:00,398
Where is Barton now?

161
00:15:00,399 --> 00:15:02,107
<i>- We don't know.
- But he's alive?</i>

162
00:15:02,109 --> 00:15:04,895
We think so. I'll brief you on
everything when you get back.

163
00:15:05,153 --> 00:15:07,193
But first, we need you to
talk to the big guy.

164
00:15:07,405 --> 00:15:10,490
Coulson, you know that Stark trusts me
about as far as he can throw me.

165
00:15:10,701 --> 00:15:14,200
I've got Stark. You get the big guy.

166
00:15:38,937 --> 00:15:40,397
Who are you?

167
00:15:40,398 --> 00:15:41,606
Get out!

168
00:15:41,607 --> 00:15:44,099
There is sickness here!

169
00:15:44,235 --> 00:15:46,235
You're a doctor.

170
00:15:46,947 --> 00:15:48,364
My father's not waking up!

171
00:15:48,365 --> 00:15:50,323
He has a fever and he's moaning

172
00:15:50,325 --> 00:15:51,533
but his eyes won't open.

173
00:15:51,534 --> 00:15:53,534
Slow down.

174
00:15:54,078 --> 00:15:56,078
My father...

175
00:15:57,540 --> 00:15:59,540
Like them?

176
00:16:02,546 --> 00:16:04,546
Please.

177
00:16:30,991 --> 00:16:33,280
You should've got paid
up front, Banner.

178
00:16:33,494 --> 00:16:34,912
You know, for a man

179
00:16:34,913 --> 00:16:36,413
who's supposed to be avoiding stress

180
00:16:36,413 --> 00:16:39,664
you picked a hell of a place to settle.

181
00:16:41,419 --> 00:16:43,625
Avoiding stress isn't the secret.

182
00:16:43,838 --> 00:16:46,330
Then what is it? Yoga?

183
00:16:47,509 --> 00:16:50,676
You brought me to the edge of
the city. Smart.

184
00:16:51,263 --> 00:16:55,307
I assume the whole place
is surrounded.

185
00:16:55,768 --> 00:16:57,768
Just you and me.

186
00:16:58,394 --> 00:17:00,434
And your actress buddy?

187
00:17:00,647 --> 00:17:02,647
Is she a spy, too?
They start that young?

188
00:17:03,024 --> 00:17:04,483
I did.

189
00:17:04,484 --> 00:17:05,734
Who are you?

190
00:17:05,736 --> 00:17:07,736
Natasha Romanoff.

191
00:17:10,199 --> 00:17:11,741
Are you here to kill me, Ms Romanoff?

192
00:17:11,742 --> 00:17:14,448
Because that's not going to
work out for everyone.

193
00:17:14,662 --> 00:17:17,117
No, of course not. I'm here
on behalf of S.H.I.E.L.D.

194
00:17:18,875 --> 00:17:20,875
S.H.I.E.L.D.

195
00:17:22,170 --> 00:17:23,336
How did they find me?

196
00:17:23,336 --> 00:17:25,172
We never lost you, Doctor.

197
00:17:25,173 --> 00:17:26,381
We've kept our distance.

198
00:17:26,382 --> 00:17:28,342
Even helped keep some other
interested parties

199
00:17:28,343 --> 00:17:29,884
off your scent.

200
00:17:29,885 --> 00:17:31,010
Why?

201
00:17:31,011 --> 00:17:33,384
Nick Fury seems to trust you.

202
00:17:33,597 --> 00:17:35,597
But now we need you to come in.

203
00:17:36,183 --> 00:17:38,183
What if I say no?

204
00:17:38,269 --> 00:17:40,393
I'll persuade you.

205
00:17:42,523 --> 00:17:46,854
And what if the other guy says no?

206
00:17:47,570 --> 00:17:49,405
You've been more than a year
without an incident.

207
00:17:49,406 --> 00:17:51,979
I don't think you want to
break that streak.

208
00:17:54,202 --> 00:17:56,824
Well, I don't every time get what I want.

209
00:17:57,873 --> 00:18:00,079
Doctor, we're facing a potential
global catastrophe.

210
00:18:00,917 --> 00:18:04,038
Well, those I actively try to avoid.

211
00:18:04,380 --> 00:18:06,420
This

212
00:18:06,632 --> 00:18:09,005
is the Tesseract.

213
00:18:09,219 --> 00:18:12,006
It has the potential energy
to wipe out the planet.

214
00:18:14,849 --> 00:18:17,008
What does Fury want me to do,
swallow it?

215
00:18:17,226 --> 00:18:19,682
He wants you to find it. It's been taken.

216
00:18:20,520 --> 00:18:24,684
It emits a gamma signature
that's too weak for us to trace.

217
00:18:24,901 --> 00:18:27,818
There's no one that knows
gamma radiation like you do.

218
00:18:28,028 --> 00:18:30,817
If there was, that's where I'd be.

219
00:18:31,407 --> 00:18:33,567
So, Fury isn't after the monster?

220
00:18:33,785 --> 00:18:35,243
Not that he's told me.

221
00:18:35,244 --> 00:18:37,403
And he tells you everything?

222
00:18:38,082 --> 00:18:39,582
Talk to Fury. He needs you on this.

223
00:18:39,583 --> 00:18:40,750
He needs me in a cage?

224
00:18:40,750 --> 00:18:41,917
No one's going to put you in a...

225
00:18:41,919 --> 00:18:43,919
Stop lying to me!

226
00:18:47,132 --> 00:18:49,753
I'm sorry. That was mean.

227
00:18:50,719 --> 00:18:52,877
I just wanted to see what you'd do.

228
00:18:54,097 --> 00:18:57,051
Why don't we do this the easy way

229
00:18:57,268 --> 00:18:58,727
where you don't use that

230
00:18:58,728 --> 00:19:02,642
and the other guy
doesn't make a mess.

231
00:19:03,441 --> 00:19:05,441
Okay?

232
00:19:05,734 --> 00:19:07,734
Natasha?

233
00:19:12,741 --> 00:19:14,741
Stand down.

234
00:19:14,743 --> 00:19:16,743
<i>We're good here.</i>

235
00:19:18,122 --> 00:19:20,122
"Just you and me."

236
00:19:21,835 --> 00:19:24,407
<i>This is out of line, Director.</i>

237
00:19:24,628 --> 00:19:27,037
<i>You're dealing
with forces you can't control.</i>

238
00:19:27,465 --> 00:19:30,916
You ever been in a war,
Councilman? In a firefight?

239
00:19:31,135 --> 00:19:33,923
Did you feel
an overabundance of control?

240
00:19:34,140 --> 00:19:37,509
<i>You're saying that this Asgard
is declaring war on our planet?</i>

241
00:19:37,643 --> 00:19:40,263
Not Asgard. Loki.

242
00:19:40,479 --> 00:19:43,266
<i>He can't be working alone.
What about the other one?</i>

243
00:19:43,397 --> 00:19:44,565
<i>His brother.</i>

244
00:19:44,566 --> 00:19:46,605
Our intelligence says
Thor is not a hostile

245
00:19:46,818 --> 00:19:47,986
but he's worlds away.

246
00:19:47,987 --> 00:19:49,903
We can't depend on him to help, either.

247
00:19:49,904 --> 00:19:51,030
It's up to us.

248
00:19:51,031 --> 00:19:53,653
<i>Which is why you
should be focusing on Phase 2.</i>

249
00:19:53,826 --> 00:19:55,326
<i>It was designed for exactly this...</i>

250
00:19:55,327 --> 00:19:58,494
Phase 2 isn't ready. Our enemy is.

251
00:19:58,748 --> 00:20:00,499
We need a response team.

252
00:20:00,500 --> 00:20:02,788
<i>The Avengers Initiative was shut down.</i>

253
00:20:03,002 --> 00:20:05,002
This isn't about the Avengers.

254
00:20:05,005 --> 00:20:06,337
<i>We've seen the list.</i>

255
00:20:06,338 --> 00:20:08,545
<i>You're running the world's greatest
covert security network</i>

256
00:20:08,673 --> 00:20:10,467
<i>and you're going to leave
the fate of the human race</i>

257
00:20:10,468 --> 00:20:11,844
<i>to a handful of freaks.</i>

258
00:20:11,845 --> 00:20:13,845
I'm not leaving anything to anyone.

259
00:20:13,971 --> 00:20:16,178
We need a response team.

260
00:20:16,432 --> 00:20:19,137
These people may be isolated,
unbalanced even

261
00:20:19,353 --> 00:20:23,516
but I believe with the right push
they can be exactly what we need.

262
00:20:23,816 --> 00:20:25,316
<i>You believe?</i>

263
00:20:25,317 --> 00:20:28,900
<i>War isn't won by sentiment, Director.</i>

264
00:20:29,613 --> 00:20:32,945
No, it's won by soldiers.

265
00:20:52,595 --> 00:20:54,595
<i>There's not enough time.</i>

266
00:20:54,597 --> 00:20:56,597
<i>I got to put her in the water!</i>

267
00:21:01,520 --> 00:21:03,145
<i>You won't be alone.</i>

268
00:21:03,146 --> 00:21:05,106
<i>Oh, my God.</i>

269
00:21:05,107 --> 00:21:07,107
<i>This guy is still alive!</i>

270
00:21:31,050 --> 00:21:33,050
Trouble sleeping?

271
00:21:34,137 --> 00:21:36,807
I slept for 70 years, sir.
I think I've had my fill.

272
00:21:38,351 --> 00:21:42,265
Then you should be out,
celebrating, seeing the world.

273
00:21:48,111 --> 00:21:50,945
When I went under,
the world was at war.

274
00:21:51,155 --> 00:21:53,155
I wake up, they say we won.

275
00:21:53,699 --> 00:21:55,699
They didn't say what we lost.

276
00:21:55,826 --> 00:21:58,152
We've made some mistakes
along the way.

277
00:21:58,578 --> 00:22:00,578
Some, very recently.

278
00:22:01,790 --> 00:22:03,125
Are you here with a mission, sir?

279
00:22:03,125 --> 00:22:04,250
I am.

280
00:22:04,251 --> 00:22:06,251
Trying to get me back in the world?

281
00:22:06,421 --> 00:22:08,421
Trying to save it.

282
00:22:12,760 --> 00:22:14,760
HYDRA's secret weapon.

283
00:22:14,971 --> 00:22:17,048
Howard Stark fished that
out of the ocean

284
00:22:17,182 --> 00:22:18,849
when he was looking for you.

285
00:22:18,851 --> 00:22:20,768
He thought what we think.

286
00:22:20,769 --> 00:22:24,896
The Tesseract could be the key
to unlimited sustainable energy.

287
00:22:25,356 --> 00:22:29,189
That's something
the world sorely needs.

288
00:22:30,695 --> 00:22:32,072
Who took it from you?

289
00:22:32,073 --> 00:22:33,698
He's called Loki.

290
00:22:33,699 --> 00:22:36,320
He's not from around here.

291
00:22:36,786 --> 00:22:38,862
There's a lot we'll have to
bring you up to speed on

292
00:22:38,997 --> 00:22:40,997
if you're in.

293
00:22:41,124 --> 00:22:43,163
The world has gotten even stranger

294
00:22:43,292 --> 00:22:44,876
than you already know.

295
00:22:44,877 --> 00:22:47,451
At this point, I doubt
anything would surprise me.

296
00:22:48,088 --> 00:22:50,088
Ten bucks says you're wrong.

297
00:22:51,509 --> 00:22:53,009
There's a debriefing packet

298
00:22:53,010 --> 00:22:55,383
waiting for you back at your apartment.

299
00:22:57,766 --> 00:22:59,766
Is there anything you can
tell us about the Tesseract

300
00:22:59,809 --> 00:23:01,309
that we ought to know now?

301
00:23:01,310 --> 00:23:03,599
You should have left it in the ocean.

302
00:23:36,347 --> 00:23:39,218
<i>Good to go on this end.
The rest is up to you.</i>

303
00:23:39,433 --> 00:23:40,893
<i>You disconnected
the transmission lines?</i>

304
00:23:40,894 --> 00:23:42,018
<i>Are we off the grid?</i>

305
00:23:42,019 --> 00:23:44,177
Stark Tower is about to become
a beacon

306
00:23:44,355 --> 00:23:45,939
of self-sustaining clean energy.

307
00:23:45,940 --> 00:23:47,980
<i>Well, assuming
the arc reactor takes over</i>

308
00:23:48,108 --> 00:23:49,692
<i>and it actually works.</i>

309
00:23:49,693 --> 00:23:51,487
<i>I assume.</i>

310
00:23:51,488 --> 00:23:53,488
Light her up.

311
00:23:58,036 --> 00:23:59,202
<i>How does it look?</i>

312
00:23:59,203 --> 00:24:01,874
Like Christmas, but with more me.

313
00:24:02,082 --> 00:24:04,041
<i>We've got to go wider on
the public awareness campaign.</i>

314
00:24:04,042 --> 00:24:05,710
<i>You need to do some press.</i>

315
00:24:05,711 --> 00:24:06,877
<i>I'm in DC tomorrow,</i>

316
00:24:06,878 --> 00:24:08,547
<i>I'm working on the zoning
for the next three buildings.</i>

317
00:24:08,548 --> 00:24:10,752
<i>Pepper, you're killing me.
The moment, remember?</i>

318
00:24:10,965 --> 00:24:12,215
<i>Enjoy the moment.</i>

319
00:24:12,217 --> 00:24:14,217
<i>Get in here and I will.</i>

320
00:24:16,721 --> 00:24:19,640
<i>Sir, Agent Coulson of
S.H.I.E.L.D. Is on the line.</i>

321
00:24:20,226 --> 00:24:21,893
<i>I'm not in.</i>

322
00:24:21,894 --> 00:24:23,894
I'm actually out.

323
00:24:30,403 --> 00:24:33,025
<i>Sir, I'm afraid he's insisting.</i>

324
00:24:33,240 --> 00:24:35,990
Grow a spine, Jarvis. I got a date.

325
00:24:40,538 --> 00:24:43,491
Levels are holding steady, I think.

326
00:24:43,708 --> 00:24:45,866
Of course they are.
I was directly involved.

327
00:24:46,086 --> 00:24:47,419
Which brings me to my next question.

328
00:24:47,420 --> 00:24:49,420
How does it feel to be a genius?

329
00:24:49,588 --> 00:24:51,830
Well, I really wouldn't know,
now would I?

330
00:24:52,049 --> 00:24:56,547
What do you mean?
All this came from you.

331
00:24:56,763 --> 00:25:00,382
No, all this came from that.

332
00:25:00,601 --> 00:25:02,890
Give yourself some credit. Please.

333
00:25:03,103 --> 00:25:05,103
Stark Tower is your baby.

334
00:25:05,105 --> 00:25:07,477
Give yourself 12% of the credit.

335
00:25:07,941 --> 00:25:09,192
12%?

336
00:25:09,192 --> 00:25:10,442
An argument can be made for 15.

337
00:25:10,443 --> 00:25:12,237
12%? My baby?

338
00:25:12,238 --> 00:25:13,946
Well, I did do all the heavy lifting.

339
00:25:13,948 --> 00:25:15,948
Literally, I lifted the heavy things.

340
00:25:16,075 --> 00:25:18,317
And, sorry, but the security snafu?

341
00:25:18,452 --> 00:25:20,077
That was on you.

342
00:25:20,078 --> 00:25:22,154
- My private elevator...
- You mean our elevator?

343
00:25:22,373 --> 00:25:25,042
...it was teeming with sweaty workmen.

344
00:25:25,251 --> 00:25:27,576
I'm going to pay for that
comment about percentages

345
00:25:27,796 --> 00:25:29,796
in some subtle way later, aren't I?

346
00:25:30,213 --> 00:25:31,631
It's not going to be that subtle.

347
00:25:31,632 --> 00:25:33,133
I'll tell you what.

348
00:25:33,134 --> 00:25:35,589
The next building is gonna
say "Potts" on the tower.

349
00:25:35,802 --> 00:25:37,802
On the lease.

350
00:25:38,097 --> 00:25:40,221
Call your mom. Can you bunk over?

351
00:25:40,432 --> 00:25:41,892
<i>Sir, the telephone.</i>

352
00:25:41,893 --> 00:25:44,266
<i>I'm afraid my protocols
are being overridden.</i>

353
00:25:44,479 --> 00:25:46,479
<i>Mr Stark, we need to talk.</i>

354
00:25:46,731 --> 00:25:49,057
You have reached the life
model decoy of Tony Stark.

355
00:25:49,317 --> 00:25:51,317
<i>- Please leave a message.
- This is urgent.</i>

356
00:25:51,487 --> 00:25:53,487
Then leave it urgently.

357
00:25:54,824 --> 00:25:56,157
Security breach. It's on you.

358
00:25:56,159 --> 00:25:58,862
- Mr Stark.
- Phil! Come in.

359
00:25:59,036 --> 00:26:00,161
"Phil"?

360
00:26:00,162 --> 00:26:01,412
I can't stay.

361
00:26:01,413 --> 00:26:02,829
His first name is "Agent."

362
00:26:02,830 --> 00:26:04,665
Come on in. We're celebrating.

363
00:26:04,666 --> 00:26:06,666
Which is why he can't stay.

364
00:26:06,669 --> 00:26:08,669
We need you to look this over
as soon as possible.

365
00:26:08,837 --> 00:26:10,087
I don't like being handed things.

366
00:26:10,088 --> 00:26:11,756
That's fine, because
I love to be handed things.

367
00:26:11,757 --> 00:26:13,757
So, let's trade.

368
00:26:14,469 --> 00:26:16,469
Thank you.

369
00:26:17,180 --> 00:26:19,385
Official consulting hours
are between 8 and 5

370
00:26:19,516 --> 00:26:20,682
every other Thursday.

371
00:26:20,683 --> 00:26:21,808
This isn't a consultation.

372
00:26:21,809 --> 00:26:23,477
Is this about the Avengers?

373
00:26:23,478 --> 00:26:25,478
Which I know nothing about.

374
00:26:25,520 --> 00:26:28,058
The Avengers Initiative
was scrapped, I thought.

375
00:26:28,273 --> 00:26:29,857
And I didn't even qualify.

376
00:26:29,858 --> 00:26:31,026
I didn't know that either.

377
00:26:31,027 --> 00:26:33,897
Apparently I'm volatile, self-obsessed,

378
00:26:34,029 --> 00:26:35,573
don't play well with others.

379
00:26:35,574 --> 00:26:36,699
That I did know.

380
00:26:36,700 --> 00:26:38,491
This isn't about personality
profiles any more.

381
00:26:38,492 --> 00:26:40,818
Whatever. Ms Potts, got a second?

382
00:26:41,038 --> 00:26:43,038
Half a mo.

383
00:26:47,336 --> 00:26:49,662
You know, I thought we were
having a moment.

384
00:26:49,881 --> 00:26:51,881
I was having 12% of a moment.

385
00:26:52,673 --> 00:26:55,130
This seems serious.
Phil's pretty shaken.

386
00:26:55,344 --> 00:26:57,344
How would you know if it's...
Why is he "Phil"?

387
00:26:57,512 --> 00:26:59,471
What is all this?

388
00:26:59,472 --> 00:27:01,472
This is

389
00:27:01,726 --> 00:27:03,726
this.

390
00:27:10,067 --> 00:27:11,567
I'm going to take the jet to DC tonight.

391
00:27:11,568 --> 00:27:12,736
Tomorrow.

392
00:27:12,737 --> 00:27:15,026
You have homework.
You have a lot of homework.

393
00:27:15,240 --> 00:27:17,240
Well, what if I didn't?

394
00:27:17,576 --> 00:27:19,159
- Lf you didn't?
- Yeah.

395
00:27:19,160 --> 00:27:21,317
You mean when you've finished?

396
00:27:22,413 --> 00:27:25,699
Well, then...

397
00:27:30,922 --> 00:27:32,922
Square deal. Fly safe.

398
00:27:36,427 --> 00:27:38,427
Work hard.

399
00:27:40,432 --> 00:27:42,392
So, any chance
you're driving by LaGuardia?

400
00:27:42,393 --> 00:27:45,144
- I can drop you.
- Fantastic.

401
00:27:45,270 --> 00:27:46,394
I want to hear

402
00:27:46,395 --> 00:27:48,271
about the cellist. Is that still a thing?

403
00:27:48,272 --> 00:27:49,606
She moved back to Portland.

404
00:27:49,607 --> 00:27:52,728
What? Boo!

405
00:28:00,787 --> 00:28:03,193
We're about 40 minutes
out from home base, sir.

406
00:28:06,917 --> 00:28:10,583
So, this Dr Banner was trying
to replicate the serum they used on me?

407
00:28:10,797 --> 00:28:12,547
A lot of people were.

408
00:28:12,548 --> 00:28:14,548
You were the world's first superhero.

409
00:28:14,884 --> 00:28:17,588
Banner thought gamma radiation
might hold the key to unlocking

410
00:28:17,761 --> 00:28:19,761
Erskine's original formula.

411
00:28:20,140 --> 00:28:21,932
Didn't really go his way, did it?

412
00:28:21,932 --> 00:28:23,601
Not so much.

413
00:28:23,602 --> 00:28:26,436
When he's not that thing, though,
the guy's like a Stephen Hawking.

414
00:28:28,481 --> 00:28:31,019
He's like a smart person.

415
00:28:33,153 --> 00:28:34,612
I gotta say,

416
00:28:34,613 --> 00:28:37,020
it's an honour to meet you officially.

417
00:28:37,782 --> 00:28:39,451
I've sort of met you. I mean,

418
00:28:39,451 --> 00:28:41,451
I watched you while you were sleeping.

419
00:28:43,079 --> 00:28:45,286
I mean, I was present

420
00:28:45,499 --> 00:28:48,785
while you were
unconscious from the ice.

421
00:28:49,002 --> 00:28:51,291
You know, it's really just a huge honour

422
00:28:51,422 --> 00:28:53,422
to have you on board this...

423
00:28:53,758 --> 00:28:55,758
I hope I'm the man for the job.

424
00:28:55,843 --> 00:28:58,713
Oh, you are. Absolutely.

425
00:28:58,930 --> 00:29:01,800
We made some modifications
to the uniform.

426
00:29:02,017 --> 00:29:03,726
I had a little design input.

427
00:29:03,727 --> 00:29:05,185
The uniform?

428
00:29:05,186 --> 00:29:07,676
Aren't the stars and stripes a little

429
00:29:08,855 --> 00:29:10,855
old-fashioned?

430
00:29:11,025 --> 00:29:13,183
With everything that's happening

431
00:29:13,403 --> 00:29:15,403
and the things that are about
to come to light,

432
00:29:15,904 --> 00:29:19,356
people might just need
a little old-fashioned.

433
00:29:51,901 --> 00:29:54,855
The Chitauri grow restless.

434
00:29:55,070 --> 00:29:56,905
Let them gird themselves.

435
00:29:56,906 --> 00:29:58,906
I will lead them in the glorious battle.

436
00:29:58,909 --> 00:30:00,909
Battle?

437
00:30:00,910 --> 00:30:03,993
Against the meagre might of Earth?

438
00:30:04,204 --> 00:30:07,039
Glorious, not lengthy.

439
00:30:07,250 --> 00:30:11,034
If your force
is as formidable as you claim.

440
00:30:11,253 --> 00:30:13,744
You question us?

441
00:30:13,964 --> 00:30:16,088
You question him,

442
00:30:16,259 --> 00:30:18,714
he who put the sceptre in your hand?

443
00:30:18,929 --> 00:30:21,846
Who gave you ancient knowledge
and new purpose

444
00:30:22,057 --> 00:30:24,928
when you were cast out, defeated?

445
00:30:25,144 --> 00:30:27,144
I was a king!

446
00:30:27,230 --> 00:30:29,434
The rightful king of Asgard,

447
00:30:29,940 --> 00:30:31,606
betrayed.

448
00:30:31,607 --> 00:30:34,230
Your ambition is little

449
00:30:34,444 --> 00:30:37,197
and born of childish need.

450
00:30:37,405 --> 00:30:39,405
We look beyond the Earth

451
00:30:39,616 --> 00:30:42,570
to the greater worlds
the Tesseract will unveil.

452
00:30:43,037 --> 00:30:45,037
You don't have the Tesseract yet.

453
00:30:47,250 --> 00:30:49,250
I don't threaten.

454
00:30:49,794 --> 00:30:52,367
But until I open the doors,

455
00:30:52,588 --> 00:30:56,205
until your force is mine to command,

456
00:30:56,968 --> 00:30:58,968
you are but words.

457
00:30:58,970 --> 00:31:02,920
You will have your war, Asgardian.

458
00:31:04,726 --> 00:31:06,726
If you fail,

459
00:31:07,729 --> 00:31:12,106
if the Tesseract is kept from us,

460
00:31:12,317 --> 00:31:16,694
there will be no realm, no barren moon,

461
00:31:16,905 --> 00:31:20,191
no crevice where he cannot find you.

462
00:31:21,786 --> 00:31:24,537
You think you know pain?

463
00:31:24,746 --> 00:31:30,416
He will make you long
for something sweet as pain.

464
00:31:59,615 --> 00:32:00,782
Stow the captain's gear.

465
00:32:00,784 --> 00:32:02,784
Yes, sir.

466
00:32:03,327 --> 00:32:06,448
Agent Romanoff, Captain Rogers.

467
00:32:06,664 --> 00:32:08,124
- Ma'am.
- Hi.

468
00:32:08,125 --> 00:32:09,250
They need you on the bridge.

469
00:32:09,250 --> 00:32:10,960
They're starting the face-trace.

470
00:32:10,961 --> 00:32:12,961
See you there.

471
00:32:13,798 --> 00:32:17,924
It was quite the buzz around here,
finding you in the ice.

472
00:32:18,218 --> 00:32:20,791
I thought Coulson was gonna swoon.

473
00:32:21,012 --> 00:32:23,884
Did he ask you to sign
his Captain America trading cards yet?

474
00:32:24,098 --> 00:32:25,517
Trading cards?

475
00:32:25,518 --> 00:32:27,675
They're vintage. He's very proud.

476
00:32:29,438 --> 00:32:31,438
Dr Banner.

477
00:32:32,733 --> 00:32:34,567
Yeah, hi.

478
00:32:34,568 --> 00:32:35,986
They told me you would be coming.

479
00:32:35,987 --> 00:32:37,987
Word is, you can find the Cube.

480
00:32:38,323 --> 00:32:40,323
Is that the only word on me?

481
00:32:40,616 --> 00:32:42,616
Only word I care about.

482
00:32:44,369 --> 00:32:46,955
It must be strange for you, all of this.

483
00:32:47,664 --> 00:32:50,335
Well, this is actually kind of familiar.

484
00:32:50,542 --> 00:32:53,116
Gentlemen, you might want
to step inside in a minute.

485
00:32:53,337 --> 00:32:56,089
It's going to get a little hard to breathe.

486
00:32:57,342 --> 00:32:59,342
<i>Flight crew, secure the deck.</i>

487
00:33:03,390 --> 00:33:05,390
Is this a submarine?

488
00:33:05,518 --> 00:33:06,643
Really?

489
00:33:06,644 --> 00:33:10,392
They want me in a submerged,
pressurised, metal container?

490
00:33:36,799 --> 00:33:39,171
No, no, this is much worse.

491
00:34:08,998 --> 00:34:11,704
Hover power check complete.
Position cyclic.

492
00:34:11,918 --> 00:34:14,327
Increase collective to 8.0%.

493
00:34:19,427 --> 00:34:21,715
Preparing for maximum
performance takeoff.

494
00:34:21,846 --> 00:34:23,514
Increase output to capacity.

495
00:34:23,514 --> 00:34:25,637
Power plant performing at capacity.

496
00:34:25,849 --> 00:34:27,518
We are clear.

497
00:34:27,518 --> 00:34:29,228
All engines operating.

498
00:34:29,228 --> 00:34:33,855
S.H.I.E.L.D. Emergency
Protocol 193.6 in effect.

499
00:34:34,108 --> 00:34:36,646
- We are at level, sir.
- Good.

500
00:34:37,027 --> 00:34:38,237
Let's vanish.

501
00:34:38,237 --> 00:34:40,644
Engage retro-reflection panels.

502
00:34:56,423 --> 00:34:58,215
Reflection panels engaged.

503
00:34:58,217 --> 00:35:00,217
Gentlemen.

504
00:35:11,938 --> 00:35:13,938
Doctor, thank you for coming.

505
00:35:15,068 --> 00:35:17,068
Thanks for asking nicely.

506
00:35:17,152 --> 00:35:19,775
So, how long am I staying?

507
00:35:19,989 --> 00:35:21,907
Once we get our hands on
the Tesseract,

508
00:35:21,907 --> 00:35:23,242
you're in the wind.

509
00:35:23,242 --> 00:35:25,242
Where are you with that?

510
00:35:25,286 --> 00:35:27,161
We're sweeping every
wirelessly accessible

511
00:35:27,163 --> 00:35:28,746
camera on the planet.

512
00:35:28,748 --> 00:35:30,748
Cell phones, laptops...

513
00:35:31,083 --> 00:35:34,369
If it's connected to a satellite,
it's eyes and ears for us.

514
00:35:34,586 --> 00:35:36,045
That's still not gonna find them in time.

515
00:35:36,047 --> 00:35:37,255
You have to narrow your field.

516
00:35:37,257 --> 00:35:39,257
How many spectrometers
do you have access to?

517
00:35:39,425 --> 00:35:41,260
- How many are there?
- Call every lab you know.

518
00:35:41,260 --> 00:35:43,096
Tell them to put
the spectrometers on the roof

519
00:35:43,097 --> 00:35:44,764
and calibrate them for gamma rays.

520
00:35:44,764 --> 00:35:47,967
I'll rough out a tracking algorithm,
basic cluster recognition.

521
00:35:48,268 --> 00:35:50,677
At least we could rule out a few places.

522
00:35:50,938 --> 00:35:52,938
Do you have somewhere
for me to work?

523
00:35:52,981 --> 00:35:54,273
Agent Romanoff,

524
00:35:54,273 --> 00:35:56,516
could you show Dr Banner
to his laboratory, please?

525
00:35:57,652 --> 00:35:59,894
You're gonna love it, Doc.
We got all the toys.

526
00:36:00,447 --> 00:36:02,447
Put it over there.

527
00:36:04,242 --> 00:36:06,365
Where did you find all these people?

528
00:36:06,579 --> 00:36:09,532
S.H.I.E.L.D. Has no shortage
of enemies, Doctor.

529
00:36:09,998 --> 00:36:11,250
Is this the stuff you need?

530
00:36:11,251 --> 00:36:12,418
Yeah, iridium.

531
00:36:12,418 --> 00:36:15,039
It's found in meteorites.
It forms anti-protons.

532
00:36:15,255 --> 00:36:17,088
It's very hard to get hold of.

533
00:36:17,090 --> 00:36:18,840
Especially if S.H.I.E.L.D.
Knows you need it.

534
00:36:18,842 --> 00:36:20,425
Well, I didn't know.

535
00:36:20,425 --> 00:36:21,842
Hey!

536
00:36:21,844 --> 00:36:24,132
The Tesseract has shown me so much.

537
00:36:24,597 --> 00:36:26,597
It's more than knowledge. It's truth.

538
00:36:26,641 --> 00:36:28,474
I know.

539
00:36:28,476 --> 00:36:30,476
What did it show you, Agent Barton?

540
00:36:31,353 --> 00:36:32,938
My next target.

541
00:36:32,938 --> 00:36:34,938
Tell me what you need.

542
00:36:37,443 --> 00:36:39,443
I need a distraction.

543
00:36:40,197 --> 00:36:42,197
And an eyeball.

544
00:36:48,371 --> 00:36:50,909
I mean, if it's not too much trouble.

545
00:36:51,125 --> 00:36:53,125
No, no. It's fine.

546
00:36:55,211 --> 00:36:57,005
It's a vintage set.

547
00:36:57,005 --> 00:36:59,295
It took me a couple of years
to collect them all.

548
00:37:01,844 --> 00:37:03,135
Near mint.

549
00:37:03,137 --> 00:37:04,721
Slight foxing around the edges, but...

550
00:37:04,722 --> 00:37:07,344
We got a hit. A 67% match.

551
00:37:07,851 --> 00:37:09,851
Wait. Cross match, 79%.

552
00:37:10,478 --> 00:37:11,644
Location?

553
00:37:11,646 --> 00:37:14,681
Stuttgart, Germany. 28 KÃ¶nigstrasse.

554
00:37:14,898 --> 00:37:16,358
He's not exactly hiding.

555
00:37:16,358 --> 00:37:17,818
Captain,

556
00:37:17,818 --> 00:37:19,818
you're up.

557
00:39:54,356 --> 00:39:56,356
Kneel before me.

558
00:39:59,943 --> 00:40:01,943
I said

559
00:40:03,322 --> 00:40:05,481
kneel!

560
00:40:14,793 --> 00:40:18,163
Is not this simpler?

561
00:40:19,715 --> 00:40:22,918
Is this not your natural state?

562
00:40:25,219 --> 00:40:28,423
It's the unspoken truth of humanity,

563
00:40:28,639 --> 00:40:31,012
that you crave subjugation.

564
00:40:31,559 --> 00:40:35,344
The bright lure of freedom
diminishes your life's joy

565
00:40:35,563 --> 00:40:38,137
in a mad scramble for power,

566
00:40:39,985 --> 00:40:41,985
for identity.

567
00:40:43,030 --> 00:40:46,364
You were made to be ruled.

568
00:40:46,992 --> 00:40:48,869
In the end,

569
00:40:48,869 --> 00:40:51,157
you will always kneel.

570
00:40:58,545 --> 00:41:00,545
Not to men like you.

571
00:41:01,550 --> 00:41:03,550
There are no men like me.

572
00:41:04,344 --> 00:41:07,215
There are always men like you.

573
00:41:08,514 --> 00:41:10,514
Look to your elder, people.

574
00:41:12,561 --> 00:41:14,561
Let him be an example.

575
00:41:20,777 --> 00:41:23,351
You know, the last time
I was in Germany,

576
00:41:23,572 --> 00:41:26,739
and saw a man standing
above everybody else,

577
00:41:26,951 --> 00:41:28,617
we ended up disagreeing.

578
00:41:28,619 --> 00:41:30,619
The soldier.

579
00:41:32,623 --> 00:41:34,458
The man out of time.

580
00:41:34,458 --> 00:41:36,458
I'm not the one who's out of time.

581
00:41:39,213 --> 00:41:41,751
<i>Loki, drop the weapon
and stand down.</i>

582
00:42:02,112 --> 00:42:03,820
Kneel.

583
00:42:03,822 --> 00:42:05,822
Not today!

584
00:42:07,326 --> 00:42:09,326
The guy's all over the place.

585
00:42:12,121 --> 00:42:14,447
<i>Agent Romanoff. You miss me?</i>

586
00:42:31,184 --> 00:42:32,643
<i>Make your move, Reindeer Games.</i>

587
00:42:32,643 --> 00:42:34,643
<i>Make your move, Reindeer Games.</i>

588
00:42:41,318 --> 00:42:43,318
<i>Good move.</i>

589
00:42:44,280 --> 00:42:46,239
Mr Stark.

590
00:42:46,240 --> 00:42:48,240
<i>Captain.</i>

591
00:42:54,625 --> 00:42:56,458
<i>Is he saying anything?</i>

592
00:42:56,460 --> 00:42:58,001
Not a word.

593
00:42:58,003 --> 00:43:00,003
<i>Just get him here. We're low on time.</i>

594
00:43:02,967 --> 00:43:04,342
I don't like it.

595
00:43:04,342 --> 00:43:06,342
What, Rock of Ages
giving up so easily?

596
00:43:06,510 --> 00:43:08,346
I don't remember it being that easy.

597
00:43:08,347 --> 00:43:10,014
This guy packs a wallop.

598
00:43:10,014 --> 00:43:13,597
Still, you are pretty spry
for an older fellow.

599
00:43:14,644 --> 00:43:16,396
What's your thing, Pilates?

600
00:43:16,396 --> 00:43:17,563
What?

601
00:43:17,565 --> 00:43:18,690
It's like calisthenics.

602
00:43:18,690 --> 00:43:20,731
You might have missed
a couple of things

603
00:43:20,943 --> 00:43:22,943
doing time as a Capsicle.

604
00:43:24,489 --> 00:43:26,280
Fury didn't tell me
he was calling you in.

605
00:43:26,282 --> 00:43:29,152
Yeah, there's a lot of things
Fury doesn't tell you.

606
00:43:29,536 --> 00:43:31,536
Where's this coming from?

607
00:43:35,208 --> 00:43:37,780
What's the matter? Are you
scared of a little lightning?

608
00:43:38,210 --> 00:43:40,500
I'm not overly fond of what follows.

609
00:43:58,315 --> 00:44:00,315
What are you doing?

610
00:44:12,413 --> 00:44:14,079
<i>And now there's that guy.</i>

611
00:44:14,081 --> 00:44:16,041
Another Asgardian?

612
00:44:16,041 --> 00:44:18,041
<i>- That guy's a friendly?
- Doesn't matter.</i>

613
00:44:18,085 --> 00:44:20,659
<i>If he frees Loki or kills him,
the Tesseract's lost.</i>

614
00:44:20,880 --> 00:44:22,880
Stark, we need a plan of attack!

615
00:44:22,923 --> 00:44:25,213
<i>I have a plan. Attack.</i>

616
00:44:31,224 --> 00:44:33,224
I'd sit this one out, Cap.

617
00:44:33,226 --> 00:44:34,434
I don't see how I can.

618
00:44:34,436 --> 00:44:37,056
These guys come from legend.
They're basically gods.

619
00:44:37,521 --> 00:44:38,938
There's only one God, ma'am.

620
00:44:38,940 --> 00:44:41,313
And I'm pretty sure
he doesn't dress like that.

621
00:44:56,791 --> 00:44:58,376
Where is the Tesseract?

622
00:44:58,376 --> 00:44:59,876
I missed you, too.

623
00:44:59,878 --> 00:45:01,878
Do I look to be in a gaming mood?

624
00:45:02,255 --> 00:45:04,090
You should thank me.

625
00:45:04,090 --> 00:45:06,130
With the Bifrost gone,
how much dark energy

626
00:45:06,344 --> 00:45:09,096
did the Allfather have to
muster to conjure you here

627
00:45:09,304 --> 00:45:11,304
to your precious Earth?

628
00:45:14,811 --> 00:45:16,811
I thought you dead.

629
00:45:17,731 --> 00:45:19,606
Did you mourn?

630
00:45:19,608 --> 00:45:21,608
We all did. Our father...

631
00:45:21,733 --> 00:45:24,652
Your father.

632
00:45:26,530 --> 00:45:29,402
He did tell you
my true parentage, did he not?

633
00:45:31,952 --> 00:45:34,195
We were raised together.

634
00:45:34,414 --> 00:45:37,036
We played together,
we fought together.

635
00:45:37,543 --> 00:45:38,960
Do you remember none of that?

636
00:45:38,960 --> 00:45:40,960
I remember a shadow.

637
00:45:42,422 --> 00:45:45,458
Living in the shade of your greatness.

638
00:45:46,177 --> 00:45:48,797
I remember you tossing me
into an abyss.

639
00:45:48,929 --> 00:45:50,929
I, who was, and should be, king!

640
00:45:51,139 --> 00:45:53,215
So you take the world I love
as a recompense

641
00:45:53,349 --> 00:45:55,349
for your imagined slights?

642
00:45:55,393 --> 00:45:58,478
No. The Earth is under
my protection, Loki.

643
00:45:59,898 --> 00:46:03,434
And you're doing
a marvellous job with that.

644
00:46:03,902 --> 00:46:05,902
The humans slaughter
each other in droves

645
00:46:05,989 --> 00:46:07,989
while you idly fret.

646
00:46:07,990 --> 00:46:10,148
I mean to rule them,
as why should I not?

647
00:46:10,367 --> 00:46:12,367
You think yourself above them?

648
00:46:12,996 --> 00:46:14,204
Well, yes.

649
00:46:14,206 --> 00:46:16,659
Then you miss the truth
of ruling, brother.

650
00:46:17,500 --> 00:46:19,500
A throne would suit you ill.

651
00:46:24,090 --> 00:46:26,842
I've seen worlds
you've never known about!

652
00:46:27,052 --> 00:46:31,215
I have grown, Odinson, in my exile.

653
00:46:31,597 --> 00:46:33,597
I have seen the true power
of the Tesseract,

654
00:46:33,684 --> 00:46:34,976
and when I wield it...

655
00:46:34,976 --> 00:46:36,976
Who showed you this power?

656
00:46:37,896 --> 00:46:39,438
Who controls the would-be king?

657
00:46:39,440 --> 00:46:41,440
- I am a king!
- Not here!

658
00:46:41,442 --> 00:46:42,858
You give up the Tesseract!

659
00:46:42,858 --> 00:46:45,396
You give up this poisonous dream!

660
00:46:48,114 --> 00:46:50,114
You come home.

661
00:46:54,454 --> 00:46:56,454
I don't have it.

662
00:46:57,666 --> 00:46:59,585
You need the Cube to bring me home.

663
00:46:59,585 --> 00:47:01,911
But I've sent it off, I know not where.

664
00:47:03,047 --> 00:47:05,047
You listen well, brother.

665
00:47:06,842 --> 00:47:08,842
I'm listening.

666
00:47:17,186 --> 00:47:19,063
Do not touch me again.

667
00:47:19,063 --> 00:47:20,856
Then don't take my stuff.

668
00:47:20,856 --> 00:47:23,099
You have no idea
what you're dealing with.

669
00:47:24,987 --> 00:47:26,987
Shakespeare in the Park?

670
00:47:27,364 --> 00:47:30,483
Doth Mother know
you wear-eth her drapes?

671
00:47:30,742 --> 00:47:33,494
This is beyond you, metal man.

672
00:47:33,704 --> 00:47:35,826
Loki will face Asgardian justice.

673
00:47:36,039 --> 00:47:39,407
He gives up the Cube,
he's all yours. Until then,

674
00:47:39,793 --> 00:47:41,793
<i>stay out of the way.</i>

675
00:47:42,588 --> 00:47:44,588
<i>Tourist.</i>

676
00:47:49,594 --> 00:47:51,594
Okay.

677
00:48:20,418 --> 00:48:23,336
Power at 400% capacity.

678
00:48:23,547 --> 00:48:25,547
How about that?

679
00:49:25,402 --> 00:49:27,402
Hey!

680
00:49:29,155 --> 00:49:31,155
That's enough.

681
00:49:34,244 --> 00:49:36,161
Now, I don't know
what you plan on doing here.

682
00:49:36,163 --> 00:49:38,452
I've come here to put an end
to Loki's schemes.

683
00:49:38,666 --> 00:49:41,204
Then prove it. Put that hammer down.

684
00:49:41,335 --> 00:49:42,585
Yeah... No.

685
00:49:42,586 --> 00:49:44,586
<i>Bad call. He loves his hammer.</i>

686
00:49:45,632 --> 00:49:47,873
You want me to put the hammer down?

687
00:50:15,246 --> 00:50:17,246
Are we done, here?

688
00:51:04,797 --> 00:51:07,751
In case it's unclear,

689
00:51:08,467 --> 00:51:10,467
if you try to escape,

690
00:51:11,344 --> 00:51:13,632
if you so much as scratch that glass,

691
00:51:23,231 --> 00:51:27,181
it's 30,000 feet straight down
in a steel trap.

692
00:51:27,737 --> 00:51:29,860
You get how that works?

693
00:51:31,907 --> 00:51:34,530
Ant, boot.

694
00:51:37,873 --> 00:51:39,873
It's an impressive cage.

695
00:51:40,541 --> 00:51:43,163
Not built, I think, for me.

696
00:51:43,543 --> 00:51:45,952
Built for something
a lot stronger than you.

697
00:51:46,172 --> 00:51:48,172
Oh, I've heard.

698
00:51:49,050 --> 00:51:51,050
<i>A mindless beast.</i>

699
00:51:51,219 --> 00:51:53,219
<i>Makes play he's still a man.</i>

700
00:51:53,929 --> 00:51:56,172
<i>How desperate are you,</i>

701
00:51:56,391 --> 00:51:59,476
<i>that you call on such
lost creatures to defend you?</i>

702
00:51:59,686 --> 00:52:02,012
<i>How desperate am I?</i>

703
00:52:02,231 --> 00:52:04,231
You threaten my world with war.

704
00:52:04,233 --> 00:52:06,356
You steal a force
you can't hope to control.

705
00:52:06,568 --> 00:52:10,351
You talk about peace,
and you kill because it's fun.

706
00:52:10,572 --> 00:52:13,572
You have made me very desperate.

707
00:52:13,784 --> 00:52:15,784
You might not be glad that you did.

708
00:52:18,956 --> 00:52:22,242
It burns you to have come so close.

709
00:52:23,710 --> 00:52:26,416
To have the Tesseract, to have power,

710
00:52:27,215 --> 00:52:29,422
unlimited power.

711
00:52:29,634 --> 00:52:31,634
And for what?

712
00:52:33,262 --> 00:52:33,969
A warm light for all mankind to share.

713
00:52:33,971 --> 00:52:37,056
A warm light for all mankind to share.

714
00:52:37,307 --> 00:52:40,557
And then to be reminded
what real power is.

715
00:52:44,648 --> 00:52:48,943
Well, let me know if "real power"
wants a magazine or something.

716
00:52:57,288 --> 00:52:58,954
He really grows on you, doesn't he?

717
00:52:58,956 --> 00:53:00,956
Loki's gonna drag this out.

718
00:53:01,083 --> 00:53:04,534
So, Thor, what's his play?

719
00:53:04,753 --> 00:53:07,291
He has an army called the Chitauri.

720
00:53:07,505 --> 00:53:10,423
They're not of Asgard,
nor any world known.

721
00:53:10,842 --> 00:53:12,918
He means to lead them
against your people.

722
00:53:13,137 --> 00:53:14,846
They will win him the Earth,

723
00:53:14,847 --> 00:53:16,847
in return, I suspect, for the Tesseract.

724
00:53:16,849 --> 00:53:18,809
An army

725
00:53:18,809 --> 00:53:20,686
from outer space.

726
00:53:20,686 --> 00:53:23,094
So, he's building another portal.

727
00:53:23,315 --> 00:53:24,773
That's what he needs Erik Selvig for.

728
00:53:24,773 --> 00:53:25,940
Selvig?

729
00:53:25,942 --> 00:53:28,266
- He's an astrophysicist.
- He's a friend.

730
00:53:28,485 --> 00:53:30,608
Loki has him under some kind of spell,

731
00:53:30,780 --> 00:53:32,489
along with one of ours.

732
00:53:32,489 --> 00:53:34,199
I want to know why Loki let us take him.

733
00:53:34,199 --> 00:53:35,701
He's not leading an army from here.

734
00:53:35,702 --> 00:53:37,619
I don't think
we should be focusing on Loki.

735
00:53:37,621 --> 00:53:39,538
That guy's brain is a bag full of cats.

736
00:53:39,539 --> 00:53:41,039
You could smell crazy on him.

737
00:53:41,041 --> 00:53:43,041
Have care how you speak.

738
00:53:43,335 --> 00:53:45,541
Loki is beyond reason,
but he is of Asgard.

739
00:53:45,963 --> 00:53:47,255
And he is my brother.

740
00:53:47,255 --> 00:53:49,255
He killed 80 people in two days.

741
00:53:50,009 --> 00:53:51,175
He's adopted.

742
00:53:51,177 --> 00:53:53,465
I think it's about the mechanics.

743
00:53:53,679 --> 00:53:55,679
Iridium... What do they
need the iridium for?

744
00:53:55,847 --> 00:53:57,014
It's a stabilising agent.

745
00:53:57,014 --> 00:53:58,431
I'm just saying, pick a weekend.

746
00:53:58,432 --> 00:54:00,184
I'll fly you to Portland.

747
00:54:00,184 --> 00:54:01,936
Keep love alive.

748
00:54:01,936 --> 00:54:03,936
It means the portal
won't collapse on itself

749
00:54:03,981 --> 00:54:05,981
like it did at S.H.I.E.L.D.

750
00:54:06,025 --> 00:54:09,311
No hard feelings, Point Break.
You've got a mean swing.

751
00:54:09,528 --> 00:54:11,771
Also, it means the portal
can open as wide

752
00:54:11,989 --> 00:54:14,396
and stay open as long, as Loki wants.

753
00:54:15,117 --> 00:54:17,324
Raise the mizzenmast. Jib the topsails.

754
00:54:19,039 --> 00:54:21,039
<i>That man is playing Galaga.</i>

755
00:54:21,291 --> 00:54:24,659
He thought we wouldn't notice,
but we did.

756
00:54:26,628 --> 00:54:28,172
How does Fury even see these?

757
00:54:28,172 --> 00:54:29,465
He turns.

758
00:54:29,465 --> 00:54:31,465
Sounds exhausting.

759
00:54:32,177 --> 00:54:33,552
The rest of the raw materials,

760
00:54:33,552 --> 00:54:36,340
Agent Barton can get
his hands on pretty easily.

761
00:54:36,556 --> 00:54:38,139
The only major component
he still needs

762
00:54:38,141 --> 00:54:41,641
is a power source
of high-energy density.

763
00:54:41,853 --> 00:54:45,103
Something to kick-start the Cube.

764
00:54:45,315 --> 00:54:48,269
When did you become an expert
in thermonuclear astrophysics?

765
00:54:48,485 --> 00:54:49,985
Last night.

766
00:54:49,985 --> 00:54:53,190
The packet, Selvig's notes,
the extraction theory papers.

767
00:54:53,407 --> 00:54:54,574
Am I the only one who did the reading?

768
00:54:54,574 --> 00:54:57,362
Does Loki need any particular
kind of power source?

769
00:54:57,577 --> 00:55:00,282
He would have to heat the Cube
to 120-million Kelvin

770
00:55:00,498 --> 00:55:02,164
just to break through
the Coulomb barrier.

771
00:55:02,166 --> 00:55:04,373
Unless Selvig has figured out
how to stabilise

772
00:55:04,585 --> 00:55:05,918
the quantum tunnelling effect.

773
00:55:05,920 --> 00:55:07,086
Well, if he could do that,

774
00:55:07,088 --> 00:55:09,543
he could achieve heavy ion fusion
at any reactor on the planet.

775
00:55:09,757 --> 00:55:12,164
Finally, someone who speaks English.

776
00:55:12,385 --> 00:55:14,385
Is that what just happened?

777
00:55:14,554 --> 00:55:16,554
It's good to meet you, Dr Banner.

778
00:55:16,764 --> 00:55:19,800
Your work on antielectron
collisions is unparalleled.

779
00:55:20,018 --> 00:55:22,018
And I'm a huge fan of the way
you lose control

780
00:55:22,019 --> 00:55:24,059
and turn into an enormous
green rage-monster.

781
00:55:25,606 --> 00:55:26,856
Thanks.

782
00:55:26,858 --> 00:55:29,349
Dr Banner is only here
to track the Cube.

783
00:55:29,568 --> 00:55:31,070
I was hoping you might join him.

784
00:55:31,070 --> 00:55:32,362
I would start with that stick of his.

785
00:55:32,364 --> 00:55:33,530
It may be magical,

786
00:55:33,532 --> 00:55:34,949
but it works an awful lot
like a HYDRA weapon.

787
00:55:34,949 --> 00:55:37,987
I don't know about that,
but it is powered by the Cube.

788
00:55:38,286 --> 00:55:40,246
And I would like to know
how Loki used it

789
00:55:40,246 --> 00:55:41,956
to turn two of the sharpest men I know

790
00:55:41,958 --> 00:55:43,958
into his personal flying monkeys.

791
00:55:44,126 --> 00:55:45,793
Monkeys? I do not understand.

792
00:55:45,793 --> 00:55:47,793
I do.

793
00:55:49,797 --> 00:55:51,797
I understood that reference.

794
00:55:52,592 --> 00:55:54,135
Shall we play, Doctor?

795
00:55:54,135 --> 00:55:56,135
This way, sir.

796
00:56:09,820 --> 00:56:11,610
The gamma readings
are definitely consistent

797
00:56:11,612 --> 00:56:13,612
with Selvig's reports of the Tesseract.

798
00:56:13,989 --> 00:56:15,824
But it's going to take weeks to process.

799
00:56:15,824 --> 00:56:17,159
If we bypass their mainframe

800
00:56:17,159 --> 00:56:18,659
and direct route to the Homer cluster,

801
00:56:18,661 --> 00:56:21,746
we can clock this
at around 600 teraflops.

802
00:56:22,916 --> 00:56:24,916
All I packed was a toothbrush.

803
00:56:25,960 --> 00:56:27,753
You know, you should come by
Stark Tower sometime.

804
00:56:27,755 --> 00:56:29,793
Top ten floors, all R&D.

805
00:56:30,132 --> 00:56:31,800
You'd love it. It's Candy Land.

806
00:56:31,800 --> 00:56:34,291
Thanks, but the last time
I was in New York,

807
00:56:34,512 --> 00:56:37,048
I kind of broke Harlem.

808
00:56:37,264 --> 00:56:39,264
Well, I promise
a stress-free environment.

809
00:56:39,307 --> 00:56:41,307
No tension, no surprises.

810
00:56:42,603 --> 00:56:44,311
- Hey!
- Nothing?

811
00:56:44,313 --> 00:56:45,438
Are you nuts?

812
00:56:45,438 --> 00:56:46,563
Jury's out.

813
00:56:46,565 --> 00:56:47,815
You really have got
a lid on it, haven't you?

814
00:56:47,817 --> 00:56:48,942
What's your secret?

815
00:56:48,943 --> 00:56:50,568
Mellow jazz, bongo drums,
huge bag of weed?

816
00:56:50,570 --> 00:56:51,987
Is everything a joke to you?

817
00:56:51,987 --> 00:56:53,112
Funny things are.

818
00:56:53,114 --> 00:56:54,989
Threatening the safety
of everyone on this ship

819
00:56:54,990 --> 00:56:56,365
isn't funny.

820
00:56:56,367 --> 00:56:57,492
No offence, Doc.

821
00:56:57,494 --> 00:56:59,119
It's all right,
I wouldn't have come aboard

822
00:56:59,119 --> 00:57:01,956
if I couldn't handle pointy things.

823
00:57:02,081 --> 00:57:04,653
You're tip-toeing, big man.
You need to strut.

824
00:57:04,791 --> 00:57:06,585
And you need to focus
on the problem, Mr Stark.

825
00:57:06,585 --> 00:57:08,210
Do you think I'm not?

826
00:57:08,211 --> 00:57:11,000
Why did Fury call us in?
Why now? Why not before?

827
00:57:11,132 --> 00:57:13,007
What isn't he telling us?

828
00:57:13,009 --> 00:57:15,009
I can't do the equation unless
I have all the variables.

829
00:57:15,387 --> 00:57:16,762
You think Fury's hiding something?

830
00:57:16,762 --> 00:57:19,929
He's a spy. Captain, he's "the" spy.

831
00:57:20,057 --> 00:57:21,934
His secrets have secrets.

832
00:57:21,934 --> 00:57:23,934
It's bugging him, too. Isn't it?

833
00:57:26,023 --> 00:57:27,940
I just want to finish my work here, and...

834
00:57:27,942 --> 00:57:29,942
Doctor?

835
00:57:34,364 --> 00:57:36,737
"A warm light for all mankind."

836
00:57:36,867 --> 00:57:38,943
Loki's jab at Fury about the Cube.

837
00:57:39,077 --> 00:57:40,661
I heard it.

838
00:57:40,663 --> 00:57:42,952
I think that was meant for you.

839
00:57:43,666 --> 00:57:46,619
Even if Barton didn't
tell Loki about the tower,

840
00:57:46,753 --> 00:57:47,960
it was still all over the news.

841
00:57:47,961 --> 00:57:50,038
The Stark Tower? That big, ugly

842
00:57:51,382 --> 00:57:52,757
building in New York?

843
00:57:52,759 --> 00:57:56,460
It's powered by an arc reactor,
a self-sustaining energy source.

844
00:57:56,596 --> 00:57:59,003
That building will run itself
for, what, a year?

845
00:57:59,139 --> 00:58:01,099
It's just the prototype.

846
00:58:01,099 --> 00:58:03,099
I'm kind of the only name
in clean energy right now.

847
00:58:03,478 --> 00:58:05,019
That's what he's getting at.

848
00:58:05,021 --> 00:58:07,594
So, why didn't S.H.I.E.L.D. Bring him in
on the Tesseract project?

849
00:58:07,731 --> 00:58:09,608
What are they doing
in the energy business

850
00:58:09,608 --> 00:58:11,068
in the first place?

851
00:58:11,068 --> 00:58:14,023
I should probably look into that
once my decryption programme

852
00:58:14,155 --> 00:58:16,313
finishes breaking into all of
S.H.I.E.L.D.'s secure files.

853
00:58:16,449 --> 00:58:17,574
I'm sorry. Did you say...

854
00:58:17,576 --> 00:58:19,576
Jarvis has been running it
since I hit the bridge.

855
00:58:19,702 --> 00:58:21,413
In a few hours,
I'll know every dirty secret

856
00:58:21,414 --> 00:58:22,706
S.H.I.E.L.D. Has ever tried to hide.

857
00:58:22,706 --> 00:58:23,831
Blueberry?

858
00:58:23,833 --> 00:58:25,833
Yet you're confused about why
they didn't want you around.

859
00:58:25,833 --> 00:58:28,668
An intelligence organisation
that fears intelligence?

860
00:58:28,795 --> 00:58:30,505
Historically, not awesome.

861
00:58:30,505 --> 00:58:32,795
I think Loki's trying to wind us up.

862
00:58:32,925 --> 00:58:34,634
This is a man who means to start a war

863
00:58:34,635 --> 00:58:36,635
and if we don't stay focused,
he'll succeed.

864
00:58:37,471 --> 00:58:39,927
We have orders.
We should follow them.

865
00:58:40,432 --> 00:58:42,432
Following's not really my style.

866
00:58:43,644 --> 00:58:46,016
And you're all about style, aren't you?

867
00:58:46,146 --> 00:58:47,313
Of the people in this room,

868
00:58:47,315 --> 00:58:49,023
which one is,
A, wearing a spangly outfit,

869
00:58:49,025 --> 00:58:50,483
and, B, not of use?

870
00:58:50,485 --> 00:58:54,813
Steve, tell me none of this
smells a little funky to you.

871
00:58:57,532 --> 00:58:59,532
Just find the Cube.

872
00:59:11,507 --> 00:59:13,507
That's the guy
my dad never shut up about?

873
00:59:13,884 --> 00:59:16,672
I'm wondering if they shouldn't have
kept him on ice.

874
00:59:17,512 --> 00:59:19,346
The guy's not wrong about Loki.

875
00:59:19,347 --> 00:59:21,222
He does have the jump on us.

876
00:59:21,224 --> 00:59:23,929
What he's got is an Acme dynamite kit.

877
00:59:24,061 --> 00:59:26,019
It's going to blow up in his face.

878
00:59:26,021 --> 00:59:28,309
And I'm going to be there when it does.

879
00:59:28,606 --> 00:59:30,766
Yeah. I'll read all about it.

880
00:59:32,903 --> 00:59:34,903
Or you'll be suiting up
with the rest of us.

881
00:59:35,782 --> 00:59:39,364
You see, I don't get a suit of armour.

882
00:59:39,494 --> 00:59:42,827
I'm exposed. Like a nerve.

883
00:59:42,956 --> 00:59:44,831
It's a nightmare.

884
00:59:44,833 --> 00:59:47,619
I've got a cluster of shrapnel
trying every second

885
00:59:47,751 --> 00:59:49,751
to crawl its way into my heart.

886
00:59:49,878 --> 00:59:51,918
This stops it.

887
00:59:52,047 --> 00:59:54,373
This little circle of light,
it's part of me now,

888
00:59:55,592 --> 00:59:57,592
not just armour.

889
00:59:57,929 --> 01:00:00,385
It's a terrible privilege.

890
01:00:00,724 --> 01:00:03,096
- But you can control it.
- Because I learned how.

891
01:00:03,226 --> 01:00:04,559
It's different.

892
01:00:04,561 --> 01:00:07,894
Hey, I read all about your accident.

893
01:00:08,023 --> 01:00:11,356
That much gamma exposure
should have killed you.

894
01:00:11,485 --> 01:00:13,940
So you're saying that the Hulk...

895
01:00:15,405 --> 01:00:17,777
The other guy saved my life?

896
01:00:18,282 --> 01:00:20,282
That's nice.

897
01:00:20,284 --> 01:00:24,070
It's a nice sentiment. Saved it for what?

898
01:00:25,373 --> 01:00:27,373
I guess we'll find out.

899
01:00:29,003 --> 01:00:30,795
You may not enjoy that.

900
01:00:30,797 --> 01:00:32,797
And you just might.

901
01:01:31,985 --> 01:01:33,485
<i>As soon as Loki took the doctor,</i>

902
01:01:33,487 --> 01:01:35,362
we moved Jane Foster.

903
01:01:35,362 --> 01:01:37,735
They've got an excellent
observatory in TromsÅ.

904
01:01:37,864 --> 01:01:41,400
She was asked to consult there
very suddenly yesterday.

905
01:01:41,536 --> 01:01:45,320
Handsome fee, private plane,
very remote.

906
01:01:46,208 --> 01:01:47,373
She'll be safe.

907
01:01:47,375 --> 01:01:49,375
Thank you.

908
01:01:50,545 --> 01:01:52,585
It's no accident, Loki taking Erik Selvig.

909
01:01:53,590 --> 01:01:56,164
I dread what he plans for him
once he's done.

910
01:01:56,302 --> 01:01:57,552
Erik is a good man.

911
01:01:57,552 --> 01:01:59,552
He talks about you a lot.

912
01:02:00,431 --> 01:02:02,431
You changed his life.

913
01:02:04,141 --> 01:02:06,141
You changed everything around here.

914
01:02:06,144 --> 01:02:08,268
They were better as they were.

915
01:02:08,856 --> 01:02:10,931
We pretend on Asgard
that we're more advanced

916
01:02:11,065 --> 01:02:14,766
but we come here,
battling like bilge snipe.

917
01:02:14,903 --> 01:02:16,862
- Like what?
- Bilge snipe.

918
01:02:16,864 --> 01:02:19,900
You know, huge, scaly, big antlers.

919
01:02:20,702 --> 01:02:22,619
- You don't have those?
- I don't think so.

920
01:02:22,619 --> 01:02:24,619
Well, they are repulsive.

921
01:02:25,831 --> 01:02:28,074
And they trample everything
in their path.

922
01:02:35,757 --> 01:02:39,092
When I first came to Earth,
Loki's rage followed me here,

923
01:02:39,221 --> 01:02:41,545
and your people paid the price.

924
01:02:41,681 --> 01:02:43,681
And now, again.

925
01:02:46,018 --> 01:02:48,474
In my youth, I courted war.

926
01:02:50,231 --> 01:02:52,231
War hasn't started yet.

927
01:02:53,360 --> 01:02:55,277
You think you could make Loki tell us

928
01:02:55,278 --> 01:02:56,695
where the Tesseract is?

929
01:02:56,695 --> 01:02:59,947
I do not know. Loki's mind is far afield.

930
01:03:00,074 --> 01:03:04,784
It's not just power he craves,
it's vengeance, upon me.

931
01:03:04,914 --> 01:03:07,036
There's no pain
would prise his need from him.

932
01:03:08,125 --> 01:03:10,331
A lot of guys think that

933
01:03:10,460 --> 01:03:12,460
until the pain starts.

934
01:03:14,257 --> 01:03:15,882
What are you asking me to do?

935
01:03:15,884 --> 01:03:19,467
I'm asking,
what are you prepared to do?

936
01:03:19,596 --> 01:03:20,762
Loki is a prisoner.

937
01:03:20,764 --> 01:03:23,088
Then why do I feel like
he's the only person on this boat

938
01:03:23,224 --> 01:03:25,224
that wants to be here?

939
01:03:37,405 --> 01:03:40,489
There's not many people
who can sneak up on me.

940
01:03:40,617 --> 01:03:42,617
But you figured I'd come.

941
01:03:42,952 --> 01:03:44,952
After.

942
01:03:45,414 --> 01:03:48,829
After whatever tortures
Fury can concoct,

943
01:03:48,960 --> 01:03:52,623
you would appear
as a friend, as a balm.

944
01:03:53,588 --> 01:03:55,380
And I would cooperate.

945
01:03:55,382 --> 01:03:57,382
I want to know what
you've done to Agent Barton.

946
01:03:57,509 --> 01:03:59,509
I would say I've expanded his mind.

947
01:04:02,097 --> 01:04:04,097
And once you've won,

948
01:04:04,891 --> 01:04:06,891
once you're king of the mountain,

949
01:04:08,313 --> 01:04:10,804
what happens to his mind?

950
01:04:12,067 --> 01:04:13,983
Is this love, Agent Romanoff?

951
01:04:13,985 --> 01:04:16,820
Love is for children. I owe him a debt.

952
01:04:20,699 --> 01:04:22,699
Tell me.

953
01:04:26,914 --> 01:04:30,164
Before I worked for S.H.I.E.L. D... I...

954
01:04:32,588 --> 01:04:36,501
Well, I made a name for myself.

955
01:04:36,634 --> 01:04:39,635
I have a very specific skill set.

956
01:04:39,762 --> 01:04:43,427
I didn't care who I used it for, or on.

957
01:04:44,432 --> 01:04:47,931
I got on S.H.I.E.L.D.'s radar
in a bad way.

958
01:04:49,103 --> 01:04:52,021
Agent Barton was sent to kill me.

959
01:04:53,067 --> 01:04:55,067
He made a different call.

960
01:04:56,570 --> 01:04:59,606
And what will you do
if I vow to spare him?

961
01:04:59,990 --> 01:05:01,449
Not let you out.

962
01:05:01,451 --> 01:05:03,451
No, but I like this.

963
01:05:04,244 --> 01:05:07,661
Your world in the balance,
and you bargain for one man.

964
01:05:07,791 --> 01:05:09,867
Regimes fall every day.

965
01:05:10,001 --> 01:05:12,539
I tend not to weep over that.
I'm Russian.

966
01:05:12,670 --> 01:05:14,670
Or I was.

967
01:05:14,963 --> 01:05:16,963
And what are you now?

968
01:05:17,090 --> 01:05:20,045
It's really not that complicated.

969
01:05:20,177 --> 01:05:24,257
I got red in my ledger,
I'd like to wipe it out.

970
01:05:25,266 --> 01:05:27,266
Can you?

971
01:05:28,144 --> 01:05:31,929
Can you wipe out that much red?

972
01:05:33,108 --> 01:05:35,108
Dreykov's daughter,

973
01:05:36,320 --> 01:05:38,320
SÄo Paulo,

974
01:05:39,197 --> 01:05:41,688
the hospital fire?

975
01:05:42,534 --> 01:05:44,907
Barton told me everything.

976
01:05:45,036 --> 01:05:48,121
Your ledger is dripping. It's gushing red

977
01:05:48,248 --> 01:05:50,739
and you think saving a man
no more virtuous than yourself

978
01:05:50,876 --> 01:05:52,376
will change anything?

979
01:05:52,378 --> 01:05:55,047
This is the basest sentimentality.

980
01:05:55,172 --> 01:05:57,414
This is a child at prayer.

981
01:05:57,550 --> 01:05:59,550
Pathetic!

982
01:05:59,635 --> 01:06:02,208
<i>You lie and kill</i>

983
01:06:02,347 --> 01:06:05,382
<i>in the service of liars and killers.</i>

984
01:06:08,478 --> 01:06:11,644
<i>You pretend to be separate,
to have your own code,</i>

985
01:06:11,773 --> 01:06:14,478
<i>something that makes up
for the horrors.</i>

986
01:06:15,652 --> 01:06:18,059
<i>But they are part of you.</i>

987
01:06:18,195 --> 01:06:21,981
<i>And they will never go away.</i>

988
01:06:22,576 --> 01:06:26,076
I won't touch Barton,
not until I make him kill you.

989
01:06:26,204 --> 01:06:28,447
Slowly, intimately,

990
01:06:28,581 --> 01:06:30,954
in every way he knows you fear.

991
01:06:31,085 --> 01:06:34,168
And then he'll wake just long
enough to see his good work

992
01:06:34,295 --> 01:06:37,746
and when he screams, I'll split his skull.

993
01:06:37,882 --> 01:06:41,003
This is my bargain, you mewling quim.

994
01:06:42,596 --> 01:06:44,596
You're a monster.

995
01:06:46,391 --> 01:06:48,391
Oh, no.

996
01:06:48,769 --> 01:06:50,769
You brought the monster.

997
01:06:53,358 --> 01:06:55,358
So, Banner.

998
01:06:55,985 --> 01:06:57,277
That's your play.

999
01:06:57,278 --> 01:06:59,278
What?

1000
01:06:59,280 --> 01:07:01,072
Loki means to unleash the Hulk.

1001
01:07:01,072 --> 01:07:02,657
Keep Banner in the lab. I'm on my way.

1002
01:07:02,657 --> 01:07:04,657
Send Thor as well.

1003
01:07:05,411 --> 01:07:06,869
Thank you

1004
01:07:06,871 --> 01:07:09,030
for your cooperation.

1005
01:07:16,547 --> 01:07:18,132
What are you doing, Mr Stark?

1006
01:07:18,132 --> 01:07:20,625
Kind of been wondering
the same thing about you.

1007
01:07:20,760 --> 01:07:22,760
You're supposed to be locating
the Tesseract.

1008
01:07:22,762 --> 01:07:24,472
We are. The model's locked

1009
01:07:24,472 --> 01:07:25,891
and we're sweeping
for the signature now.

1010
01:07:25,891 --> 01:07:27,016
When we get a hit,

1011
01:07:27,016 --> 01:07:29,016
we'll have the location
within half a mile.

1012
01:07:29,101 --> 01:07:31,605
Yeah, then you get your
Cube back. No muss, no fuss.

1013
01:07:31,605 --> 01:07:33,481
Yeah, then you get your
Cube back. No muss, no fuss.

1014
01:07:33,481 --> 01:07:35,481
What is "Phase 2"?

1015
01:07:36,818 --> 01:07:39,653
Phase 2 is S.H.I.E.L.D. Uses
the Cube to make weapons.

1016
01:07:39,780 --> 01:07:41,655
Sorry, computer was moving
a little slow for me.

1017
01:07:41,657 --> 01:07:44,362
Rogers, we gathered everything
related to the Tesseract.

1018
01:07:44,494 --> 01:07:46,077
This does not mean that we're making...

1019
01:07:46,079 --> 01:07:47,204
I'm sorry, Nick.

1020
01:07:47,204 --> 01:07:49,494
What were you lying?

1021
01:07:49,623 --> 01:07:51,000
I was wrong, Director.

1022
01:07:51,001 --> 01:07:52,168
The world hasn't changed a bit.

1023
01:07:52,168 --> 01:07:53,335
Did you know about this?

1024
01:07:53,335 --> 01:07:54,793
You want to think about
removing yourself

1025
01:07:54,795 --> 01:07:56,253
from this environment, Doctor?

1026
01:07:56,255 --> 01:07:58,414
I was in Calcutta.
I was pretty well removed.

1027
01:07:58,548 --> 01:07:59,842
Loki is manipulating you.

1028
01:07:59,842 --> 01:08:01,552
And you've been doing what, exactly?

1029
01:08:01,552 --> 01:08:03,344
You didn't come here because
I bat my eyelashes at you.

1030
01:08:03,346 --> 01:08:04,597
Yes, and I'm not leaving

1031
01:08:04,597 --> 01:08:06,014
because suddenly
you get a little twitchy.

1032
01:08:06,016 --> 01:08:07,766
I'd like to know why S.H.I.E.L.D.

1033
01:08:07,768 --> 01:08:11,467
Is using the Tesseract
to build weapons of mass destruction.

1034
01:08:12,106 --> 01:08:14,106
Because of him.

1035
01:08:14,525 --> 01:08:16,484
Me?

1036
01:08:16,484 --> 01:08:18,858
Last year, Earth had a visitor
from another planet

1037
01:08:18,988 --> 01:08:22,154
who had a grudge match
that levelled a small town.

1038
01:08:22,282 --> 01:08:24,488
We learned that
not only are we not alone

1039
01:08:24,618 --> 01:08:28,201
but we are hopelessly,
hilariously, outgunned.

1040
01:08:28,329 --> 01:08:30,572
My people want nothing
but peace with your planet.

1041
01:08:30,707 --> 01:08:32,707
But you're not the only people
out there, are you?

1042
01:08:32,792 --> 01:08:34,792
And you're not the only threat.

1043
01:08:34,878 --> 01:08:38,046
The world's filling up with
people who can't be matched,

1044
01:08:38,716 --> 01:08:40,050
that can't be controlled.

1045
01:08:40,051 --> 01:08:41,301
Like you controlled the Cube?

1046
01:08:41,301 --> 01:08:42,677
Your work with the Tesseract

1047
01:08:42,679 --> 01:08:45,252
is what drew Loki to it, and his allies.

1048
01:08:45,390 --> 01:08:46,890
It is a signal to all the realms

1049
01:08:46,891 --> 01:08:49,560
that the Earth is ready
for a higher form of war.

1050
01:08:49,685 --> 01:08:50,894
A higher form?

1051
01:08:50,895 --> 01:08:52,020
You forced our hand.

1052
01:08:52,020 --> 01:08:53,145
We had to come up with something.

1053
01:08:53,146 --> 01:08:54,273
A nuclear deterrent.

1054
01:08:54,274 --> 01:08:56,274
Because that always
calms everything right down.

1055
01:08:56,400 --> 01:08:58,773
Remind me again how
you made your fortune, Stark.

1056
01:08:58,904 --> 01:09:01,275
I'm sure if he still made weapons,
Stark would be neck-deep...

1057
01:09:01,405 --> 01:09:03,157
Hold on. How is this now about me?

1058
01:09:03,158 --> 01:09:04,408
I'm sorry, isn't everything?

1059
01:09:04,408 --> 01:09:06,408
I thought humans were
more evolved than this.

1060
01:09:06,412 --> 01:09:09,282
Excuse me, did we come to
your planet and blow stuff up?

1061
01:09:09,414 --> 01:09:11,414
You treat your champions
with such mistrust.

1062
01:09:11,417 --> 01:09:13,001
