1171
01:15:44,113 --> 01:15:46,113
Thanks.

1172
01:15:48,743 --> 01:15:50,743
Stark!

1173
01:15:52,622 --> 01:15:54,414
Stark, I'm here!

1174
01:15:54,416 --> 01:15:56,416
<i>Good.</i>

1175
01:15:57,127 --> 01:15:59,127
<i>Let's see what we've got.</i>

1176
01:15:59,253 --> 01:16:01,046
I got to get this
superconducting coolant system

1177
01:16:01,046 --> 01:16:02,171
back online

1178
01:16:02,172 --> 01:16:03,756
before I can access the rotors,

1179
01:16:03,757 --> 01:16:05,757
work on dislodging the debris.

1180
01:16:08,137 --> 01:16:09,805
<i>I need you to get to that
engine control panel</i>

1181
01:16:09,805 --> 01:16:13,470
<i>and tell me which relays
are in overload position.</i>

1182
01:16:25,780 --> 01:16:27,780
<i>What does it look like in there?</i>

1183
01:16:28,033 --> 01:16:30,570
It seems to run
on some form of electricity.

1184
01:16:30,702 --> 01:16:32,702
Well, you're not wrong.

1185
01:17:36,270 --> 01:17:39,105
We are not your enemies, Banner.

1186
01:17:39,231 --> 01:17:41,231
Try to think!

1187
01:17:50,368 --> 01:17:52,368
<i>Okay, the relays are intact.</i>

1188
01:17:52,369 --> 01:17:53,953
