The idea was to bring together a group

1280
01:30:26,354 --> 01:30:28,893
of remarkable people

1281
01:30:29,692 --> 01:30:32,527
to see if they could become
something more.

1282
01:30:33,904 --> 01:30:38,069
To see if they could work together
when we needed them to,

1283
01:30:38,201 --> 01:30:41,534
to fight the battles that we never could.

1284
01:30:44,291 --> 01:30:49,118
Phil Coulson died
still believing in that idea.

1285
01:30:51,465 --> 01:30:53,465
In heroes.

1286
01:31:01,225 --> 01:31:03,225
Well,

1287
01:31:03,644 --> 01:31:06,314
it's an old-fashioned notion.

1288
01:31:26,626 --> 01:31:29,117
<i>You fell out of the sky.</i>

1289
01:31:43,144 --> 01:31:44,769
Did I hurt anybody?

1290
01:31:44,770 --> 01:31:47,805
There's nobody around here to get hurt.

1291
01:31:47,939 --> 01:31:51,225
You did scare the hell
out of some pigeons, though.

1292
01:31:52,069 --> 01:31:53,235
Lucky.

1293
01:31:53,237 --> 01:31:54,988
Or just good aim.

1294
01:31:54,988 --> 01:31:56,988
You were awake when you fell.

1295
01:31:58,658 --> 01:32:00,698
- You saw?
- The whole thing.

1296
01:32:00,828 --> 01:32:02,578
Right through the ceiling.

1297
01:32:02,579 --> 01:32:06,529
Big and green and buck-ass nude.

1298
01:32:06,667 --> 01:32:08,667
Here.

1299
01:32:09,170 --> 01:32:11,328
Didn't think those would
fit you until you shrunk down

1300
01:32:11,463 --> 01:32:13,872
to a regular-size feller.

1301
01:32:16,219 --> 01:32:18,219
Thank you.

1302
01:32:18,512 --> 01:32:20,346
Are you an alien?

1303
01:32:20,347 --> 01:32:21,849
What?

1304
01:32:21,850 --> 01:32:23,809
From outer space, an alien.

1305
01:32:23,810 --> 01:32:25,185
No.

1306
01:32:25,185 --> 01:32:28,305
Well, then, son, you've got a condition.

1307
01:32:39,159 --> 01:32:41,484
Clint. You're going to be all right.

1308
01:32:44,831 --> 01:32:46,908
You know that?

1309
01:32:47,751 --> 01:32:49,751
Is that what you know?

1310
01:32:52,088 --> 01:32:54,960
I've got no window.

1311
01:32:55,760 --> 01:32:57,760
I have to flush him out.

1312
01:32:58,054 --> 01:33:00,012
You got to level out.
It's going to take time.

1313
01:33:00,014 --> 01:33:02,014
You don't understand.

1314
01:33:03,518 --> 01:33:06,768
Have you ever had someone
take your brain and play?

1315
01:33:07,564 --> 01:33:11,726
Pull you out
and stuff something else in?

1316
01:33:14,904 --> 01:33:17,277
Do you know what it's like
to be unmade?

1317
01:33:18,824 --> 01:33:21,197
You know that I do.

1318
01:33:28,793 --> 01:33:30,793
Why am I back?

1319
01:33:30,962 --> 01:33:32,463
How did you get him out?

1320
01:33:32,465 --> 01:33:35,300
Cognitive recalibration.

1321
01:33:35,426 --> 01:33:38,130
I hit you really hard on the head.

1322
01:33:38,261 --> 01:33:40,261
Thanks.

1323
01:33:43,641 --> 01:33:45,641
Natasha...

1324
01:33:46,061 --> 01:33:47,270
How many agents did I...

1325
01:33:47,270 --> 01:33:48,854
Don't.

1326
01:33:48,855 --> 01:33:51,063
Don't do that to yourself, Clint.

1327
01:33:51,650 --> 01:33:53,484
This is Loki.

1328
01:33:53,485 --> 01:33:56,108
This is monsters and magic,

1329
01:33:56,238 --> 01:33:57,989
and nothing we were ever trained for.

1330
01:33:57,990 --> 01:33:59,658
Loki, did he get away?

1331
01:33:59,658 --> 01:34:00,993
Yeah.

1332
01:34:00,993 --> 01:34:03,234
I don't suppose you know where.

1333
01:34:03,371 --> 01:34:05,287
I didn't need to know.

1334
01:34:05,288 --> 01:34:07,288
I didn't ask.

1335
01:34:10,295 --> 01:34:12,786
He's going to
make his play soon, though.

1336
01:34:13,131 --> 01:34:14,256
Today.

1337
01:34:14,256 --> 01:34:16,256
We got to stop him.

1338
01:34:16,259 --> 01:34:17,635
Yeah? Who's "we"?

1339
01:34:17,636 --> 01:34:19,636
I don't know. Whoever's left.

1340
01:34:20,805 --> 01:34:22,805
Well,

1341
01:34:23,850 --> 01:34:26,009
if I put an arrow
through Loki's eye socket,

1342
01:34:26,145 --> 01:34:28,850
I would sleep better, I suppose.

1343
01:34:31,692 --> 01:34:33,692
Now you sound like you.

1344
01:34:33,985 --> 01:34:35,985
But you don't.

1345
01:34:37,363 --> 01:34:40,199
You're a spy, not a soldier.

1346
01:34:40,326 --> 01:34:45,070
Now you want to wade into a war. Why?

1347
01:34:46,832 --> 01:34:48,832
What did Loki do to you?

1348
01:34:49,543 --> 01:34:51,952
He didn't. I just...

1349
01:34:55,716 --> 01:34:57,716
Natasha.

1350
01:34:59,345 --> 01:35:01,345
I've been compromised.

1351
01:35:04,434 --> 01:35:06,556
I got red in my ledger.

1352
01:35:08,688 --> 01:35:10,765
I would like to wipe it out.

1353
01:35:26,789 --> 01:35:28,416
Was he married?

1354
01:35:28,417 --> 01:35:29,958
No.

1355
01:35:29,960 --> 01:35:34,171
There was a cellist, I think.

1356
01:35:35,757 --> 01:35:37,757
I'm sorry.

1357
01:35:37,885 --> 01:35:39,885
He seemed like a good man.

1358
01:35:40,846 --> 01:35:42,055
He was an idiot.

1359
01:35:42,055 --> 01:35:44,297
Why? For believing?

1360
01:35:44,434 --> 01:35:45,975
For taking on Loki alone.

1361
01:35:45,976 --> 01:35:47,811
He was doing his job.

1362
01:35:47,813 --> 01:35:50,350
He was out of his league.
He should have waited.

1363
01:35:50,481 --> 01:35:51,648
He should have...

1364
01:35:51,649 --> 01:35:53,358
Sometimes there isn't a way out, Tony.

1365
01:35:53,359 --> 01:35:55,481
Right, I've heard that before.

1366
01:35:55,610 --> 01:35:57,237
Is this the first time you lost a soldier?

1367
01:35:57,238 --> 01:35:59,238
We are not soldiers.

1368
01:36:03,494 --> 01:36:05,371
I'm not marching to Fury's fife.

1369
01:36:05,372 --> 01:36:06,663
Neither am I.

1370
01:36:06,664 --> 01:36:08,871
He's got the same blood
on his hands that Loki does.

1371
01:36:09,001 --> 01:36:10,501
But right now,
we got to put that behind us

1372
01:36:10,502 --> 01:36:12,708
and get this done.

1373
01:36:12,837 --> 01:36:13,962
Loki needs a power source.

1374
01:36:13,963 --> 01:36:15,090
If we can put together a list...

1375
01:36:15,091 --> 01:36:16,257
He made it personal.

1376
01:36:16,259 --> 01:36:17,425
That's not the point.

1377
01:36:17,426 --> 01:36:19,797
That is the point. That's Loki's point.

1378
01:36:19,927 --> 01:36:21,927
He hit us all right where we live. Why?

1379
01:36:21,971 --> 01:36:23,096
To tear us apart.

1380
01:36:23,097 --> 01:36:25,097
Yeah, divide and conquer is great

1381
01:36:25,100 --> 01:36:27,555
but he knows he has to
take us out to win, right?

1382
01:36:27,685 --> 01:36:29,354
That's what he wants.

1383
01:36:29,354 --> 01:36:31,845
He wants to beat us,
he wants to be seen doing it.

1384
01:36:31,983 --> 01:36:33,817
He wants an audience.

1385
01:36:33,818 --> 01:36:35,610
Right. I caught his act in Stuttgart.

1386
01:36:35,612 --> 01:36:38,529
Yeah, that was just previews.
This is opening night.

1387
01:36:38,655 --> 01:36:41,194
And Loki, he's a full-tilt diva, right?

1388
01:36:41,326 --> 01:36:43,034
He wants flowers, he wants parades.

1389
01:36:43,036 --> 01:36:46,819
He wants a monument built to the skies
with his name plastered...

1390
01:36:48,582 --> 01:36:50,582
Son of a bitch.

1391
01:37:01,430 --> 01:37:02,596
Time to go.

1392
01:37:02,597 --> 01:37:04,265
- Go where?
- I'll tell you on the way.

1393
01:37:04,265 --> 01:37:06,265
Can you fly one of those jets?

1394
01:37:06,851 --> 01:37:08,851
I can.

1395
01:37:11,981 --> 01:37:13,149
You got a suit?

1396
01:37:13,149 --> 01:37:14,274
Yeah.

1397
01:37:14,275 --> 01:37:16,275
Then suit up.

1398
01:37:43,389 --> 01:37:44,805
Hey, you guys aren't
authorised to be in here.

1399
01:37:44,806 --> 01:37:47,132
Son, just don't.

1400
01:37:49,186 --> 01:37:50,311
Sir.

1401
01:37:50,313 --> 01:37:52,064
Agent Hill.

1402
01:37:52,064 --> 01:37:54,064
Those cards,

1403
01:37:55,735 --> 01:38:00,197
they were in Coulson's locker,
not in his jacket.

1404
01:38:04,619 --> 01:38:06,619
They needed the push.

1405
01:38:09,291 --> 01:38:11,579
<i>We have an unauthorised departure
from Bay 6.</i>

1406
01:38:12,461 --> 01:38:14,461
They found him.

1407
01:38:14,630 --> 01:38:18,331
Get our communications back up,
whatever you have to do.

1408
01:38:18,466 --> 01:38:20,708
- I want eyes on everything.
- Yes, sir.

1409
01:38:34,274 --> 01:38:36,150
<i>Sir, I've turned off the arc reactor</i>

1410
01:38:36,152 --> 01:38:39,984
<i>but the device
is already self-sustaining.</i>

1411
01:38:40,113 --> 01:38:42,273
<i>Shut it down, Dr Selvig.</i>

1412
01:38:42,951 --> 01:38:44,951
It's too late!

1413
01:38:46,287 --> 01:38:48,287
She can't stop now.

1414
01:38:48,789 --> 01:38:51,246
She wants to show us something!

1415
01:38:51,377 --> 01:38:53,416
A new universe.

1416
01:38:53,545 --> 01:38:55,545
<i>Okay.</i>

1417
01:39:02,136 --> 01:39:04,136
<i>The barrier is pure energy.</i>

1418
01:39:04,139 --> 01:39:06,139
<i>It's unbreachable.</i>

1419
01:39:06,140 --> 01:39:08,140
<i>Yeah, I got that.</i>

1420
01:39:09,144 --> 01:39:11,144
<i>Plan B.</i>

1421
01:39:11,313 --> 01:39:13,390
<i>Sir, the Mark 7
is not ready for deployment.</i>

1422
01:39:13,524 --> 01:39:15,765
Then skip the spinning rims.
We're on the clock.

1423
01:39:35,505 --> 01:39:38,542
Please tell me you're going
to appeal to my humanity.

1424
01:39:39,676 --> 01:39:42,047
Actually, I'm planning to threaten you.

1425
01:39:42,179 --> 01:39:43,762
You should have left
your armour on for that.

1426
01:39:43,764 --> 01:39:45,305
Yeah.

1427
01:39:45,306 --> 01:39:46,515
It's seen a bit of mileage,

1428
01:39:46,516 --> 01:39:49,137
and you've got
the glow stick of destiny.

1429
01:39:49,936 --> 01:39:52,225
Would you like a drink?

1430
01:39:52,355 --> 01:39:53,606
Stalling me won't change anything.

1431
01:39:53,608 --> 01:39:55,729
No, no. Threatening.

1432
01:39:55,859 --> 01:39:57,359
No drink? Are you sure?

1433
01:39:57,360 --> 01:39:59,360
I'm having one.

1434
01:39:59,947 --> 01:40:03,860
The Chitauri are coming.
Nothing will change that.

1435
01:40:04,743 --> 01:40:06,286
What have I to fear?

1436
01:40:06,287 --> 01:40:08,287
The Avengers.

1437
01:40:10,082 --> 01:40:12,408
That's what we call ourselves.
We're sort of like a team.

1438
01:40:12,543 --> 01:40:14,293
"Earth's mightiest heroes"-type thing.

1439
01:40:14,295 --> 01:40:16,295
Yes, I've met them.

1440
01:40:16,297 --> 01:40:17,463
Yeah.

1441
01:40:17,465 --> 01:40:18,756
It takes us a while to get any traction,

1442
01:40:18,757 --> 01:40:19,884
I'll give you that one.

1443
01:40:19,885 --> 01:40:22,090
But let's do a head count, here.

1444
01:40:22,220 --> 01:40:24,711
Your brother, the demigod,

1445
01:40:26,431 --> 01:40:30,015
a super soldier, a living legend
who kind of lives up to the legend.

1446
01:40:30,145 --> 01:40:33,311
A man with breathtaking
anger-management issues,

1447
01:40:33,439 --> 01:40:36,524
a couple of master assassins,
and you, big fella,

1448
01:40:37,152 --> 01:40:40,105
you've managed to piss off
every single one of them.

1449
01:40:40,238 --> 01:40:41,363
That was the plan.

1450
01:40:41,364 --> 01:40:43,364
Not a great plan.

1451
01:40:43,492 --> 01:40:45,532
When they come,

1452
01:40:45,661 --> 01:40:47,244
and they will,

1453
01:40:47,246 --> 01:40:48,621
they'll come for you.

1454
01:40:48,622 --> 01:40:49,747
I have an army.

1455
01:40:49,747 --> 01:40:51,414
We have a Hulk.

1456
01:40:51,416 --> 01:40:52,917
I thought the beast had wandered off.

1457
01:40:52,917 --> 01:40:54,917
You're missing the point.
There is no throne.

1458
01:40:54,962 --> 01:40:58,960
There is no version of this
where you come out on top.

1459
01:40:59,091 --> 01:41:01,417
Maybe your army comes
and maybe it's too much for us,

1460
01:41:01,551 --> 01:41:03,551
but it's all on you.

1461
01:41:04,346 --> 01:41:05,596
Because if we can't protect the Earth,

1462
01:41:05,597 --> 01:41:08,717
you can be damn well sure
we'll avenge it.

1463
01:41:10,770 --> 01:41:13,806
How will your friends have time for me

1464
01:41:13,939 --> 01:41:15,939
when they are so busy fighting you?

1465
01:41:23,158 --> 01:41:24,323
This usually works.

1466
01:41:24,324 --> 01:41:27,161
Well, performance issues,
it's not uncommon.

1467
01:41:27,287 --> 01:41:29,287
One out of five...

1468
01:41:30,666 --> 01:41:31,207
Jarvis, anytime now.

1469
01:41:31,207 --> 01:41:33,579
Jarvis, anytime now.

1470
01:41:35,337 --> 01:41:38,088
You will all fall before me.

1471
01:41:38,215 --> 01:41:39,716
Deploy!

1472
01:41:39,716 --> 01:41:41,716
Deploy!

1473
01:42:08,329 --> 01:42:11,283
<i>And there's one other
person you pissed off.</i>

1474
01:42:12,417 --> 01:42:14,417
<i>His name was Phil.</i>

1475
01:42:37,442 --> 01:42:39,068
Right.

1476
01:42:39,069 --> 01:42:41,069
Army.

1477
01:43:52,686 --> 01:43:54,104
Loki!

1478
01:43:54,104 --> 01:43:56,145
Turn off the Tesseract, or I'll destroy it.

1479
01:43:56,274 --> 01:43:57,440
You can't.

1480
01:43:57,442 --> 01:43:59,442
There is no stopping it.

1481
01:43:59,443 --> 01:44:01,360
There is only

1482
01:44:01,362 --> 01:44:02,612
the war.

1483
01:44:02,613 --> 01:44:04,613
So be it.

1484
01:44:25,845 --> 01:44:27,721
<i>Stark, we're on your three,
headed northeast.</i>

1485
01:44:27,722 --> 01:44:29,845
What? Did you stop for drive-through?

1486
01:44:29,975 --> 01:44:31,975
Swing up Park. I'm going
to lay them out for you.

1487
01:44:49,746 --> 01:44:51,204
<i>Sir, we have more incoming.</i>

1488
01:44:51,206 --> 01:44:53,206
Fine. Let's keep them occupied.

1489
01:44:59,838 --> 01:45:01,838
- Nat?
- I see him.

1490
01:45:46,052 --> 01:45:48,260
We got to get back up there.

1491
01:46:39,609 --> 01:46:41,609
Stark, are you seeing this?

1492
01:46:42,028 --> 01:46:44,483
<i>Seeing. Still working on believing.</i>

1493
01:46:44,613 --> 01:46:46,113
Where's Banner?
Has he shown up yet?

1494
01:46:46,114 --> 01:46:47,282
<i>Banner?</i>

1495
01:46:47,283 --> 01:46:49,033
Just keep me posted.

1496
01:46:49,034 --> 01:46:51,194
<i>Jarvis, find me a soft spot.</i>

1497
01:46:53,457 --> 01:46:55,457
Look at this!

1498
01:46:55,458 --> 01:46:57,458
Look around you!

1499
01:46:57,461 --> 01:47:01,328
You think this madness
will end with your rule?

1500
01:47:01,465 --> 01:47:03,465
It's too late.

1501
01:47:04,467 --> 01:47:05,844
It's too late to stop it.

1502
01:47:05,845 --> 01:47:09,711
No. We can, together.

1503
01:47:16,313 --> 01:47:18,435
Sentiment.

1504
01:47:46,011 --> 01:47:48,548
We've got civilians
still trapped up here.

1505
01:47:49,722 --> 01:47:51,722
Loki.

1506
01:48:02,359 --> 01:48:04,359
They're fish in a barrel down there.

1507
01:48:09,618 --> 01:48:11,618
We got this. It's good. Go.

1508
01:48:11,703 --> 01:48:13,203
Do you think you can hold them off?

1509
01:48:13,204 --> 01:48:15,204
Captain,

1510
01:48:16,208 --> 01:48:19,043
it would be my genuine pleasure.

1511
01:48:45,905 --> 01:48:47,905
Just like Budapest all over again.

1512
01:48:48,242 --> 01:48:50,733
You and I remember Budapest
very differently.

1513
01:49:06,886 --> 01:49:08,011
It's going to be an hour

1514
01:49:08,011 --> 01:49:09,429
before they can
scramble the National Guard.

1515
01:49:09,430 --> 01:49:11,430
National Guard?

1516
01:49:12,182 --> 01:49:13,934
Does the army know
what's happening here?

1517
01:49:13,935 --> 01:49:15,935
Do we?

1518
01:49:16,145 --> 01:49:17,479
You need men in these buildings.

1519
01:49:17,479 --> 01:49:19,105
There are people inside and
they're going to be running

1520
01:49:19,106 --> 01:49:20,440
right into the line of fire.

1521
01:49:20,442 --> 01:49:22,442
You take them to the basements
or through the subway.

1522
01:49:22,484 --> 01:49:24,194
You keep them off the streets.

1523
01:49:24,194 --> 01:49:26,815
I need a perimeter as far back as 39th.

1524
01:49:26,948 --> 01:49:28,948
Why the hell
should I take orders from you?

1525
01:49:42,631 --> 01:49:43,965
I need men in those buildings.

1526
01:49:43,966 --> 01:49:46,042
Lead the people down
and away from the streets.

1527
01:49:46,176 --> 01:49:48,750
We're going to set up a perimeter
all the way down to 39th Street.

1528
01:49:59,148 --> 01:50:00,856
Well, we got its attention.

1529
01:50:00,858 --> 01:50:02,858
<i>What the hell was step two?</i>

1530
01:50:32,265 --> 01:50:33,390
What's the story upstairs?

1531
01:50:33,391 --> 01:50:35,391
The power surrounding the Cube
is impenetrable.

1532
01:50:35,435 --> 01:50:38,056
<i>Thor's right. We got
to deal with these guys.</i>

1533
01:50:38,189 --> 01:50:39,939
- How do we do this?
- As a team.

1534
01:50:39,939 --> 01:50:41,774
I have unfinished business with Loki.

1535
01:50:41,775 --> 01:50:42,943
Yeah? Well, get in line.

1536
01:50:42,944 --> 01:50:44,068
Save it.

1537
01:50:44,069 --> 01:50:45,528
Loki's going to keep
this fight focused on us,

1538
01:50:45,529 --> 01:50:46,695
and that's what we need.

1539
01:50:46,697 --> 01:50:48,488
Without him,
these things could run wild.

1540
01:50:48,489 --> 01:50:51,444
We got Stark up top.
He's going to need us to...

1541
01:50:58,792 --> 01:51:02,577
So, this all seems horrible.

1542
01:51:03,046 --> 01:51:04,715
I've seen worse.

1543
01:51:04,716 --> 01:51:05,841
Sorry.

1544
01:51:05,841 --> 01:51:08,511
No, we could use a little worse.

1545
01:51:08,636 --> 01:51:11,043
<i>- Stark, we got him.
- Banner?</i>

1546
01:51:11,180 --> 01:51:12,555
Just like you said.

1547
01:51:12,556 --> 01:51:15,261
Then tell him to suit up.
I'm bringing the party to you.

1548
01:51:21,733 --> 01:51:23,809
I don't see how that's a party.

1549
01:51:31,659 --> 01:51:33,659
Dr Banner.

1550
01:51:34,412 --> 01:51:36,412
Now might be a really good
time for you to get angry.

1551
01:51:37,250 --> 01:51:39,703
That's my secret, Captain.

1552
01:51:41,420 --> 01:51:43,420
I'm always angry.

1553
01:51:54,141 --> 01:51:56,141
<i>Hold on!</i>

1554
01:52:25,673 --> 01:52:27,673
Send the rest.

1555
01:52:33,974 --> 01:52:35,349
Guys.

1556
01:52:35,350 --> 01:52:36,684
<i>Call it, Captain.</i>

1557
01:52:36,685 --> 01:52:37,976
All right, listen up.

1558
01:52:37,978 --> 01:52:40,765
Until we can close that portal,
our priority is containment.

1559
01:52:40,898 --> 01:52:42,356
Barton, I want you on that roof.

1560
01:52:42,358 --> 01:52:44,358
Eyes on everything.
Call out patterns and strays.

1561
01:52:44,359 --> 01:52:45,860
Stark, you got the perimeter.

1562
01:52:45,862 --> 01:52:47,154
Anything gets
more than three blocks out,

1563
01:52:47,154 --> 01:52:48,822
you turn it back or you turn it to ash.

1564
01:52:48,823 --> 01:52:50,157
<i>- Can you give me a lift?
- Right.</i>

1565
01:52:50,158 --> 01:52:52,158
<i>Better clench up, Legolas.</i>

1566
01:52:54,828 --> 01:52:57,202
Thor, you got to try
and bottleneck that portal.

1567
01:52:57,332 --> 01:52:58,623
Slow them down.

1568
01:52:58,625 --> 01:53:00,783
You got the lightning.
Light the bastards up.

1569
01:53:03,087 --> 01:53:04,837
You and me,
we stay here on the ground.

1570
01:53:04,838 --> 01:53:06,006
We keep the fighting here.

1571
01:53:06,006 --> 01:53:08,006
And Hulk...

1572
01:53:09,719 --> 01:53:11,719
Smash.

1573
01:54:04,400 --> 01:54:06,400
Sir.

1574
01:54:06,569 --> 01:54:08,569
The Council is on.

1575
01:54:12,451 --> 01:54:15,701
Stark, you got a lot of strays
sniffing your tail.

1576
01:54:17,539 --> 01:54:19,578
I'm just trying to keep them
off the streets.

1577
01:54:19,708 --> 01:54:21,949
Well, they can't bank worth a damn.

1578
01:54:22,085 --> 01:54:23,377
So find a tight corner.

1579
01:54:23,377 --> 01:54:25,377
I will roger that.

1580
01:54:47,694 --> 01:54:49,694
Oh, boy.

1581
01:54:55,869 --> 01:54:57,621
Nice call.

1582
01:54:57,622 --> 01:54:58,956
What else you got?

1583
01:54:58,957 --> 01:55:01,743
<i>Thor is taking on
a squadron down on Sixth.</i>

1584
01:55:01,877 --> 01:55:04,082
And he didn't invite me.

1585
01:55:43,586 --> 01:55:45,337
Captain, none of this
is going to mean a damn thing

1586
01:55:45,337 --> 01:55:46,712
if we don't close that portal.

1587
01:55:46,713 --> 01:55:48,506
Our biggest guns couldn't touch it.

1588
01:55:48,507 --> 01:55:50,750
Well, maybe it's not about guns.

1589
01:55:52,679 --> 01:55:54,679
If you want to get up there,
you're going to need a ride.

1590
01:55:55,724 --> 01:55:57,724
I got a ride.

1591
01:55:57,935 --> 01:55:59,935
I could use a boost, though.

1592
01:56:01,563 --> 01:56:03,021
Are you sure about this?

1593
01:56:03,023 --> 01:56:05,561
Yeah. It's gonna be fun.

1594
01:56:32,595 --> 01:56:34,595
Okay, turn, turn.

1595
01:56:34,597 --> 01:56:36,597
Less! Less!

1596
01:57:59,059 --> 01:58:02,012
<i>Captain, the bank
on 42nd past Madison.</i>

1597
01:58:02,145 --> 01:58:04,021
<i>They've cornered
a lot of civilians in there.</i>

1598
01:58:04,023 --> 01:58:06,023
I'm on it.

1599
01:58:26,045 --> 01:58:28,045
Everyone! Clear out!

1600
01:58:57,744 --> 01:58:59,537
<i>Director Fury,</i>

1601
01:58:59,537 --> 01:59:01,456
<i>the Council has made a decision.</i>

1602
01:59:01,457 --> 01:59:04,208
I recognise the Council
has made a decision.

1603
01:59:04,335 --> 01:59:06,043
But given that
it's a stupid-ass decision,

1604
01:59:06,045 --> 01:59:07,587
I have elected to ignore it.

1605
01:59:07,587 --> 01:59:10,921
<i>Director, you're closer
than any of our subs.</i>

1606
01:59:11,050 --> 01:59:12,176
<i>You scramble that jet...</i>

1607
01:59:12,176 --> 01:59:14,881
That is the island of Manhattan,
Councilman.

1608
01:59:15,012 --> 01:59:17,088
Until I'm certain my team can't hold it,

1609
01:59:17,224 --> 01:59:19,224
I will not order a nuclear strike

1610
01:59:19,350 --> 01:59:20,891
against a civilian population.

1611
01:59:20,893 --> 01:59:23,301
<i>If we don't hold them here,
we lose everything.</i>

1612
01:59:23,438 --> 01:59:26,189
If I send that bird out, we already have.

1613
01:59:29,944 --> 01:59:31,944
You.

1614
01:59:33,907 --> 01:59:35,907
Hawkeye!

1615
01:59:36,534 --> 01:59:38,453
Nat, what are you doing?

1616
01:59:38,453 --> 01:59:40,453
A little help?

1617
01:59:44,751 --> 01:59:46,751
I got him.

1618
02:00:12,320 --> 02:00:13,654
Enough!

1619
02:00:13,655 --> 02:00:16,112
You are, all of you, beneath me!

1620
02:00:16,242 --> 02:00:18,993
I am a god, you dull creature.

1621
02:00:19,119 --> 02:00:21,119
And I will not be bullied by...

1622
02:00:30,466 --> 02:00:32,466
Puny god.

1623
02:00:40,475 --> 02:00:42,475
The sceptre...

1624
02:00:43,103 --> 02:00:45,103
Doctor.

1625
02:00:46,189 --> 02:00:49,024
Loki's sceptre. The energy.

1626
02:00:49,150 --> 02:00:50,944
The Tesseract can't fight,

1627
02:00:50,944 --> 02:00:52,984
but you can't protect against yourself.

1628
02:00:53,113 --> 02:00:54,238
It's not your fault.

1629
02:00:54,239 --> 02:00:56,239
You didn't know what you were doing.

1630
02:00:58,536 --> 02:01:00,694
Actually, I think I did.

1631
02:01:00,829 --> 02:01:03,784
I built in a safety
to cut their power source.

1632
02:01:05,001 --> 02:01:06,542
Loki's sceptre.

1633
02:01:06,543 --> 02:01:09,117
It may be able to close the portal.

1634
02:01:11,215 --> 02:01:13,373
And I'm looking right at it.

1635
02:01:25,355 --> 02:01:29,222
<i>Sir, we will lose power
before we penetrate that shell.</i>

1636
02:01:35,865 --> 02:01:39,152
Jarvis, you ever hear the tale of Jonah?

1637
02:01:39,286 --> 02:01:41,658
<i>I wouldn't consider him a role model.</i>

1638
02:02:51,278 --> 02:02:53,194
<i>Director Fury is no longer in command.</i>

1639
02:02:53,195 --> 02:02:55,234
<i>Override order 7-Alpha- 1- 1.</i>

1640
02:02:55,363 --> 02:02:57,938
<i>7- Alpha- 1- 1, confirmed.
We're go for takeoff.</i>

1641
02:02:58,826 --> 02:03:00,903
Sir, we have a bird in motion!

1642
02:03:01,412 --> 02:03:03,412
Anyone on the deck,
we have a rogue bird.

1643
02:03:03,539 --> 02:03:04,957
We need to shut it down!

1644
02:03:04,957 --> 02:03:07,163
Repeat, takeoff is not authorised.

1645
02:03:37,699 --> 02:03:39,859
Stark, do you hear me?

1646
02:03:39,993 --> 02:03:42,117
You have a missile
headed straight for the city.

1647
02:03:42,663 --> 02:03:44,163
<i>How long?</i>

1648
02:03:44,164 --> 02:03:46,242
<i>Three minutes, max.</i>

1649
02:03:46,376 --> 02:03:48,127
<i>The payload will wipe out Midtown.</i>

1650
02:03:48,127 --> 02:03:50,167
Jarvis, put everything we got
into the thrusters.

1651
02:03:50,296 --> 02:03:52,296
<i>I just did.</i>

1652
02:04:04,853 --> 02:04:06,311
<i>Package is sent.</i>

1653
02:04:06,313 --> 02:04:09,432
<i>Detonation in
2 minutes, 30 seconds, mark.</i>

1654
02:04:32,215 --> 02:04:34,587
Are you ready for another bout?

1655
02:04:35,260 --> 02:04:37,260
What, are you getting sleepy?

1656
02:04:41,891 --> 02:04:43,891
Right at the crown!

1657
02:04:49,649 --> 02:04:51,567
I can close it.

1658
02:04:51,568 --> 02:04:53,606
Can anybody copy?

1659
02:04:53,737 --> 02:04:54,987
I can shut the portal down.

1660
02:04:54,988 --> 02:04:57,028
<i>- Do it!
- No, wait.</i>

1661
02:04:57,157 --> 02:04:58,533
Stark, these things are still coming.

1662
02:04:58,533 --> 02:04:59,658
I got a nuke coming in.

1663
02:04:59,659 --> 02:05:01,659
It's gonna blow in less than a minute.

1664
02:05:11,253 --> 02:05:13,253
And I know just where to put it.

1665
02:05:20,264 --> 02:05:22,636
<i>Stark, you know that's a one-way trip.</i>

1666
02:05:22,766 --> 02:05:24,266
Save the rest for the turn, J.

1667
02:05:24,268 --> 02:05:28,349
<i>Sir, shall I try Miss Potts?</i>

1668
02:05:28,480 --> 02:05:30,520
Might as well.

1669
02:05:32,444 --> 02:05:34,815
<i>The streets of New York City
have become a battleground.</i>

1670
02:05:34,945 --> 02:05:37,649
<i>The Army is here trying
to contain the violence</i>

1671
02:05:37,782 --> 02:05:39,365
<i>but clearly, it is outmatched.</i>

1672
02:05:39,367 --> 02:05:41,655
<i>And I have to say,
in all my years of reporting,</i>

1673
02:05:41,786 --> 02:05:44,703
<i>I have never seen anything like this.</i>

1674
02:05:44,831 --> 02:05:46,457
<i>We have limited information
on the team</i>

1675
02:05:46,457 --> 02:05:50,206
<i>but we do know that
billionaire Tony Stark's Iron Man...</i>

1676
02:07:03,537 --> 02:07:05,537
Come on, Stark.

1677
02:07:12,003 --> 02:07:14,003
Close it.

1678
02:07:33,193 --> 02:07:35,193
Son of a gun.

1679
02:07:38,948 --> 02:07:40,948
He's not slowing down.

1680
02:07:58,635 --> 02:08:00,635
Is he breathing?

1681
02:08:27,957 --> 02:08:29,957
What the hell?

1682
02:08:32,087 --> 02:08:34,210
What just happened?

1683
02:08:34,338 --> 02:08:36,627
Please tell me nobody kissed me.

1684
02:08:40,930 --> 02:08:42,930
We won.

1685
02:08:44,934 --> 02:08:46,350
All right, yay!

1686
02:08:46,350 --> 02:08:48,350
Hurray. Good job, guys.

1687
02:08:48,436 --> 02:08:51,640
Let's just not come in tomorrow.
Let's just take a day.

1688
02:08:52,524 --> 02:08:54,524
Have you ever tried shawarma?

1689
02:08:54,527 --> 02:08:56,814
There's a shawarma joint
about two blocks from here.

1690
02:08:56,945 --> 02:08:58,945
I don't know what it is,
but I want to try it.

1691
02:08:59,030 --> 02:09:01,030
We're not finished yet.

1692
02:09:05,454 --> 02:09:07,578
And then shawarma after.

1693
02:09:29,229 --> 02:09:31,470
If it's all the same to you,

1694
02:09:34,777 --> 02:09:36,777
I'll have that drink now.

1695
02:09:44,328 --> 02:09:46,367
<i>Despite the devastation
of what has been confirmed</i>

1696
02:09:46,497 --> 02:09:48,331
<i>as an extraterrestrial attack,</i>

1697
02:09:48,332 --> 02:09:49,998
<i>the extraordinary heroics</i>

1698
02:09:50,000 --> 02:09:52,000
<i>of the group known as the Avengers</i>

1699
02:09:52,086 --> 02:09:53,752
<i>has been to many a cause
not only for comfort,</i>

1700
02:09:53,753 --> 02:09:54,880
<i>but for celebration.</i>

1701
02:09:54,881 --> 02:09:57,287
<i>It's just really great knowing
they're out there.</i>

1702
02:09:57,425 --> 02:09:59,342
<i>That someone is watching over us.</i>

1703
02:09:59,344 --> 02:10:00,676
<i>I love you, Thor!</i>

1704
02:10:00,677 --> 02:10:02,512
<i>And then these guys were like...</i>

1705
02:10:02,514 --> 02:10:03,972
<i>And then the air goes...</i>

1706
02:10:03,974 --> 02:10:05,474
<i>And this green guy walks up
and he goes...</i>

1707
02:10:05,475 --> 02:10:06,641
<i>I don't know.</i>

1708
02:10:06,643 --> 02:10:09,097
<i>I don't exactly feel safer
with those things out there.</i>

1709
02:10:09,228 --> 02:10:12,313
<i>It just seems that there's
a lot they're not telling us.</i>

1710
02:10:12,439 --> 02:10:15,855
<i>Superheroes in New York?
Give me a break.</i>

1711
02:10:15,984 --> 02:10:17,984
<i>These so-called "heroes"</i>

1712
02:10:18,029 --> 02:10:19,447
<i>have to be held responsible</i>

1713
02:10:19,448 --> 02:10:21,605
<i>for the destruction done to this city.</i>

1714
02:10:21,742 --> 02:10:23,864
<i>This was their fight.
Where are they now?</i>

1715
02:10:23,993 --> 02:10:24,493
<i>Tough questions are being asked
about the Avengers themselves.</i>

1716
02:10:24,494 --> 02:10:26,819
<i>Tough questions are being asked
about the Avengers themselves.</i>

1717
02:10:26,956 --> 02:10:28,081
<i>Their sudden appearance</i>

1718
02:10:28,082 --> 02:10:29,582
<i>and equally sudden disappearance...</i>

1719
02:10:29,582 --> 02:10:32,371
<i>What, this is all somehow their fault?</i>

1720
02:10:34,421 --> 02:10:37,587
<i>Captain America saved my life.</i>

1721
02:10:39,717 --> 02:10:43,217
<i>Wherever he is, and
wherever any of them are,</i>

1722
02:10:43,346 --> 02:10:45,346
<i>I would just...</i>

1723
02:10:45,640 --> 02:10:47,930
<i>I would want to say thank you.</i>

1724
02:10:50,395 --> 02:10:52,021
<i>Where are the Avengers?</i>

1725
02:10:52,023 --> 02:10:54,430
I'm not currently
tracking their whereabouts.

1726
02:10:54,567 --> 02:10:56,725
I'd say they've earned
a leave of absence.

1727
02:10:56,860 --> 02:10:58,570
<i>And the Tesseract?</i>

1728
02:10:58,572 --> 02:11:00,814
<i>The Tesseract is where it belongs.</i>

1729
02:11:01,239 --> 02:11:03,565
<i>Out of our reach.</i>

1730
02:11:03,701 --> 02:11:05,368
<i>That's not your call.</i>

1731
02:11:05,369 --> 02:11:06,536
I didn't make it.

1732
02:11:06,537 --> 02:11:08,779
I just didn't argue with the god that did.

1733
02:11:08,914 --> 02:11:10,832
<i>So, you let him take it</i>

1734
02:11:10,833 --> 02:11:12,585
<i>and the war criminal, Loki,</i>

1735
02:11:12,586 --> 02:11:14,420
<i>who should be
answering for his crime.</i>

1736
02:11:14,421 --> 02:11:16,993
<i>I think he will be.</i>

1737
02:11:30,479 --> 02:11:33,148
<i>I don't think you understand
what you've started,</i>

1738
02:11:33,273 --> 02:11:35,729
<i>letting the Avengers
loose on this world.</i>

1739
02:11:36,277 --> 02:11:37,402
<i>They're dangerous.</i>

1740
02:11:37,403 --> 02:11:41,068
<i>They surely are,
and the whole world knows it.</i>

1741
02:11:41,615 --> 02:11:44,189
Every world knows it.

1742
02:11:44,618 --> 02:11:46,694
<i>Was that the point of all this?</i>

1743
02:11:46,828 --> 02:11:48,828
<i>A statement?</i>

1744
02:11:51,292 --> 02:11:53,292
<i>A promise.</i>

1745
02:12:01,469 --> 02:12:03,469
<i>Sir, how does it work now?</i>

1746
02:12:04,139 --> 02:12:06,139
They've gone their separate ways.

1747
02:12:06,265 --> 02:12:09,184
Some, pretty extremely far.

1748
02:12:09,935 --> 02:12:11,935
If we get into a situation like this again,

1749
02:12:11,979 --> 02:12:13,648
what happens then?

1750
02:12:13,649 --> 02:12:15,649
They'll come back.

1751
02:12:16,150 --> 02:12:17,985
Are you really sure about that?

1752
02:12:17,987 --> 02:12:19,987
I am.

1753
02:12:20,614 --> 02:12:22,614
Why?

1754
02:12:22,865 --> 02:12:25,072
Because we'll need them to.

1755
02:15:16,671 --> 02:15:19,162
Humans.

1756
02:15:20,466 --> 02:15:24,796
They are not the cowering
wretches we were promised.

1757
02:15:25,764 --> 02:15:27,921
They stand.

1758
02:15:28,766 --> 02:15:34,766
They are unruly,
and therefore cannot be ruled.

1759
02:15:42,197 --> 02:15:45,068
To challenge them

1760
02:15:45,199 --> 02:15:48,900
is to court death.
